statement: which fantastic four episode aired on 9/21/1968?
table_text: the fantastic four are off to carry out their experiments on a remote island. the mole man, however, has been waiting for them and traps them in a radiation field and plans to submerge the world’s largest cities. the fantastic four escape but the mole man traps them again. they manage to escape their separate ways. they foil mole man’s domination and escape the island once and for all.

the fantastic four find a ruined castle in the middle of a forest in transylvania. ben is summoned by diablo and unable to resist, opens diablo's prison, unleashing him and later brainwashing ben. diablo tricks the world into thinking he has the power to help them. the world then realises what a fraud diablo really is. the fantastic four seize this opportunity to attack diablo’s castle. after getting far in the dungeons, the four get captured. ben escapes, releases the others and they defeat diablo.

while on a television show, reed recalls the time he first met victor von doom before he became dr. doom. he had ben as his roommate at university. victor was working on dangerous experiments, especially a test that brought him to the hospital and got him expelled from university. worse than that, the test altered his face and he swore revenge on reed having to hide his work from him. ben and reed became soldiers in world war ii. ben, susan, johnny and reed all went aboard a space rocket for space exploration. and so the origin of the fantastic four began. dr. doom confronts the fantastic four on the television show and briefs them on his origin. after that dr. doom attempts to get his revenge, but fails and escapes only to crash.

the skrulls have immediately failed to destroy the fantastic four. they introduce the super-skrull who possesses double power effects the fantastic four have. the fantastic four are overwhelmed by the super-skrull’s combined powers. the fantastic four lure the super-skrull to crater island. susan plants a sonic wave jamming device on the super-skrull before he can destroy them with his ultimate power level.
klaw is here to vanquish the fantastic 4 with his solidifying sonic waves. johnny is on vacation or so it would seem and arrives in the nick of time to assist mr. fantastic in catching the klaw.

reed is competing with dr. kragoff in race to the moon for astronomical research. during the launch, dr. kragoff and his primate crew have developed some reverse energy powers. dr. kragoff is now transparent and becomes the red ghost. red ghost kidnaps susan after counter attacking. she escapes and thwarts red ghost’s attempt to eliminate her companions. using a special device, reed turns red ghost into a plastic statue.

a ufo has been sighted. the pilot abducts the fantastic four from the science center and is setting course for planet x. there, their dictator kurrgo requests the fantastic four save their planet from another planet knocked off its orbit. reed manages to formulate a working plan to save the population. while the plan is in process, kurrgo has other ideas. however, reed tricks kurrgo and leaves him on the exploding planet while the micro-sized population and the fantastic four get away to safety.

the fantastic four face a bunch of old rivals in yancy street, but their old enemy red ghost and his primates show up and capture them. during their voyage to the moon, the four turn the tables, but red ghost gets away and the four are dumped on the moon. they barely manage to get to a source of oxygen which is the watcher’s laboratory. using one of the watcher’s machines, reed brings down red ghost’s ship. susan gets dr. kragoff banished into a trans-nitron machine. reed uses that machine to get back to earth.

dr. doom challenges the fantastic four. doctor doom begins his plans by capturing susan. soon the fantastic four manage to locate and penetrate dr. doom’s flying fortress, but ben is turned back to his former self and the other three are trapped. ben turns himself back into the thing, releases the others and aborts dr. doom’s tidal waves. they chase dr. doom out and back to the flying fortress. after a struggle through the dangerous complex of the fortress, they abort dr. doom’s global destruction for good.

the fantastic four are testing their rocket when they are drawn into the skrull galaxy. after beating the first round of skrulls, the fantastic four weaken and are taken prisoner. the cruel skrull warlord morrat wishes to overthrow the skrull emperor. the warlord gives the fantastic four the option to assist them or die. reed tricks the warlord into getting him and his friends' powers fully charged. they defeat the warlord as the emperor arrives and he allows the fantastic 4 to go freely back to earth.

the fantastic four beat the criminal forces working for dr. gamma, and blow up the island with its secret weapons. while escaping, dr. gamma is infected by the radiation levels in the seabed and morphs into some creature. johnny is flustered with being moved around and quits from the fantastic four. in the town johnny goes to, there have been sightings of the gamma ray. johnny defeats the gamma ray by himself, but he comes back with the hideous giant sea monster giganto. johnny rejoins the fantastic four. ben succeeds in eliminating the sea monster. the gamma ray is defeated but not finished.

johnny finds a mysterious lady named lady dorma and takes her back to the headquarters. she claims to have come from a land beneath the sea called pacifica, which is under siege by attuma. they manage to slip past attuma’s forces. pacifica is losing hope and attuma has shadowed the seabed. triton can only fight man-to-man with attuma while his men prepare traps to weaken triton into a losing battle. the fantastic 4 thwart every trap. triton beats attuma and the forces retreat. note: due to the rights to the sub-mariner being held by grantray-lawrence animation, the adaptation of the first meeting between the ff and namor was altered. instead, prince triton, an original pastiche of namor was reworked into the namor role.

the mole man is creating earthquakes and causing buildings to sink deep into the earth. in addition, he and his moloids kidnap susan. the mole man as usual has been expecting the other three and sends them back to the surface to tell the army not to get involved. they manage to halt them and seek an alternate entrance in the underworld. johnny rescues susan, then they penetrate the laboratory. they all return the buildings to the surface and escape the exploding caves.

after coming back from vacation reed tells ben an interesting theory on attempting to restore him. they head to dr. doom’s deserted castle to use the time machine the doctor left behind. in 2000 b.c the four weaken during a fight and are taken by pharaoh rama-tut, who is a lot more than he would seem at first sight. susan is to be rama-tut’s queen while the other three are put to work with some mind control. ben turns back to his former self. as he rescues susan, he is once again the thing. the four battle rama-tut to his sphinx. finally, they destroy his sphinx and return to their own time.

the watcher has made strange events in hope of preventing the silver surfer from coming but the plan fails and the surfer summons galactus. susan assists the unconscious surfer and he begins to think differently. the watcher has a plan only johnny can undergo. reed and ben sabotage galactus' earth draining machine and the silver surfer arrives to battle galactus. this angers galactus, but johnny gets back with the weapon that makes galactus see reason not to destroy the earth. note: in the episode "galactus", susan richards (the invisible girl) has the role originated by alicia masters (explaining to the silver surfer about humanity).
the micro world of dr. doom

the fantastic four have been shrunken to small size. dr. doom is after them and takes them to the micro world. dr. doom briefs them on his micro genius experiments involving a king and a princess from the micro world. the four battle the giant guards but dr. doom catches them and imprisons them with the king and princess. they all escape and enlarge themselves. ben puts a stop to the lizard men, then the four return to their own world.

on a remote planet, its inhabitants are fighting against blastaar and are able to banish him. reed and johnny enter the dangerous space zone via dimensional transport. as they depart, blastaar escapes and follows them. blastaar is too powerful for the four to handle. they lure blastaar into an evacuated atomic power plant, where they use some atomic matter to put him in a coma. they eject him through the dimensional transport back into the space zone.

the fantastic four study a radiated meteor. the molecule man appears and threatens the public. after the fantastic four tastes some of his power, he leaves to undergo his ruling the world. reed has developed a weapon he thinks will defeat the molecule man. the weapon works, but the molecule man gets away. the fantastic four continue their pursuit. the plan to stop the molecule man is tricky. they manage to reverse the molecule man’s form with a fragment of the meteor.

the fantastic four are taken to another planet where they are regarded as criminals against evil, charged by three old enemies. reed is forced to recall his memories on klaw, molecule, man and blastaar’s defeat. meanwhile the other three escape and they rescue reed just as the verdict is given. at the surface, they have to battle the court judge before they are able to leave the planet for earth.

the imposter plans to lure the fantastic four into a trap by posing as a famous hollywood director. the four are tempted to be in a movie and briefly retell their previous adventures to the director. the next day, the four fly to the director’s island and the director blows them out of the sky. the fantastic four are forced to go through the director’s deadly movie landscapes and make it to the boat on the other side of the island which the director detonates. the imposter removes his disguise and the fantastic four surprise him. the real director prevents the imposter from escaping upon forgetting that he had locked the director in the room that imposter was escaping into. the fantastic four have no desire to be movie stars in the end.

the fantastic four receive a distress signal from planet x, where the remnants of the population need help against a new threat. they travel back and overcome environmental challenges to help. guided by an old ally, they defeat the new dictator and secure peace for the planet.

strange celestial phenomena alarm the world, pulling the fantastic four to investigate. they discover the watcher, doing damage control after an experiment gone awry. figuring out multiple dimensions, they assist the watcher in preventing a cosmic catastrophe.

the skrulls, seeking payback, secretly infiltrate earth and start causing chaos by impersonating the fantastic four members. the real four, with help from nick fury, outwit the skrulls and save earth from impending doom.

hydra uncovers an ancient device capable of citywide control. the fantastic four, infiltrating hydra's tight network, must solve a puzzle before hydra activates the device. tension rises as they race against time to deactivate it.

earth's elements go haywire, giving rise to new elemental villains. struck off guard, the fantastic four regroup and utilize scientific ingenuity to defeat each villain. managing an ambitious plan, they restore balance and win public admiration.

the fantastic four receive an anonymous tip about hidden activities on the moon. on arrival, they uncover a sinister operation involving mind control tech, battling both moon enemies and an earth faction aiming to exploit it.

a mysterious force in the everglades threatens to envelop cities around it. alert to this danger, the fantastic four traverse dangerous terrain to uncover and neutralize a bioweapon while dealing with an old foe and new swamp warriors.

an open temporal rift begins to drag historic and futuristic threats into their time. the fantastic four must navigate these disruptions, battling figures from differing eras, until they seal the portal, restoring the timeline balance.

robotic duplicates of the fantastic four run rampant, tarnishing their reputation. working against both public discontent and hidden enemies, they turn the tables on the creators of the replicants, ultimately saving their good name.

what is the length of the coastal scenic drive?
table_text: runs from concord avenue to the mystic valley parkway.
runs through tiverton, rhode island; fall river, massachusetts; westport, massachusetts

route 24 is a connector between the fall river/new bedford area east of rhode island to the boston metropolitan area, connecting the major freeways of the area: i-195 in fall river and i-93/us-1 near i-95 in randolph.\n- route 79 runs along the highway between exits 7 and 9, concurrent with route 24.\n- i-195 has a brief concurrency with route 24 in fall river.
most of us-20 between marlborough and weston runs along the boston post road.
freeway comprises the eastern 5 miles (8.0 km) of route 57, connecting route 187 to u.s. route 5 and i-91.

route 9 between worcester and boston is mostly a divided full-access highway with traffic light-controlled intersections which serves as one of the main alternatives to the massachusetts turnpike. many shopping centers, car dealers, full-service restaurants and businesses line the roadway on this stretch, especially in framingham, such as barnes & noble, marshalls, t.g.i. fridays, kohl's, toys "r" us, best buy, olive garden and walmart. this stretch of the roadway is also encompassed in the golden triangle district of massachusetts.

the central artery is the portion of i-93 in downtown boston, which runs from massachusetts ave. (just south of exit 20) north to u.s. route 1's departure at exit 27.\nroute 3 leaves the artery at exit 26.
stretches from weston/newton line to the boston public garden.

the east boston expressway comprises the first 1.2 miles (1.9 km) of route 1a's northern segment. it stretches from i-93 exit 24 at the southern end of the callahan tunnel (northbound) and the sumner tunnel (southbound) to just northeast of the interchange with route 145 in east boston, near the eastern end of the mass pike.
grand army of the republic highway
the cross-country u.s. route 6 is designated grand army of the republic highway over its entire length, which spans 3,205 miles (5,158 km).
route 88 serves as a connector running from the horseneck beach reservation north to i-195 exit 10 in westport.
route 213 is designated "loop connector." it serves as a freeway connection between interstates 93 and 495 in methuen.
route 146a in massachusetts is designated as the lydia taft highway, which runs from the rhode island state border to route 122 in uxbridge.

the mass pike is a toll road running from the new york state border to downtown boston. it serves as the main cross-state freeway connecting the western and eastern portions of the state. the "pike" carries the easternmost 138 miles (222 km) of cross-country interstate 90.

u.s. route 3 and ma route 3 connect to each other on memorial drive, which runs from the fresh pond parkway to main street.\nroute 2 travels along memorial drive with us-3 and leaves via the boston university bridge.
the mid-cape highway is the main highway on cape cod, a 36-mile (58 km) long freeway running from route 3 and the sagamore bridge east to the orleans rotary.
the 65-mile (105 km) mohawk trail comprises the western section of route 2, from the new york border east to orange, and is regarded as one of the most scenic drives in the area.
runs from the alewife brook parkway to the revere beach parkway.

this section of u.s. route 1 runs from i-93 exit 27 (tobin bridge) to an interchange with route 60 in revere. this was originally supposed to be part of i-95, but i-95 was cancelled in boston, with i-93 and us-1 taking its place.
the northwest expressway serves as a freeway connection between i-95/route 128 (exit 32a) in burlington and the f.e. everett turnpike in nashua, nh.

the pilgrims highway is the southern portion of route 3, a 42-mile (68 km) long freeway which serves as a connector between cape cod (via u.s. route 6) and the boston metropolitan area (via i-93 and i-95).\n- u.s. route 44 runs along the highway between exits 6 and 7.
the southeast expressway is the section of i-93 between the route 3 split (exit 7) and the mass ave. interchange (exit 18), where it continues into boston as the central artery.
the southern artery is a major arterial in the city of quincy, running from quincy ave to the furnace brook parkway.
taunton-new bedford expressway\n(alfred m. bessette memorial highway)
the new bedford expressway comprises the southern 19 miles (31 km) of route 140, and serves as a freeway connection between u.s. route 6 in new bedford and route 24 (exit 12) in taunton, near i-495.
route 9 in framingham is named the ted williams highway, in commemoration of late boston red sox hall-of-famer ted williams who wore the number 9 on his jersey.
i-84 in massachusetts is designated the wilbur cross highway. it runs 8 miles (13 km) from the connecticut state border to the mass pike at exit 9.

route 146 is a freeway that, along with rhode island's route 146, serves to connect the metropolitan areas of providence and worcester. the entire route starts from i-95 in providence, with the massachusetts section picking up at the state line in millville. the highway runs 21 miles (34 km) northward, intersecting the mass pike (i-90) in worcester, and terminating at i-290 shortly thereafter.\n- route 122a runs along the highway between exits 9 and 12, concurrently with route 146.

the yankee division highway consists of the route 128 beltway before it was truncated to its southern terminus in canton, and continues to span its entire length. it stretches from i-93's exit 7 in braintree to route 128's northern terminus at route 127a in gloucester.
- i-95 runs along the highway between exits 12 and 45 (concurrent with 128).
- i-93 runs along the highway between exits 1 and 7.
- u.s. route 1 runs along the highway between i-95 exit 15b and i-93 exit 7.
runs from bonded warehouse to seaport boulevard, connecting the seaport district to the financial district.
follows the picturesque coastline, offering views of the atlantic ocean and providing access to multiple beaches and state parks.
connects brush hill road to route 28, passing through the blue hills reservation offering scenic views of the surrounding woodlands.
a historical route that links various significant sites in boston including the old state house, paul revere house, and boston common.
runs along route 6a, known for its cranberry bogs and quaint towns, offering a scenic alternative to the nearby mid-cape highway.
connects downtown lowell to lawrence industrial zone, serving as an economic and transport hub for the region.
provides a mountain vista through the heart of berkshire county, highlighting the region's historical and cultural landmarks.
follows the connecticut river, offering access to several recreational areas and connecting major urban and suburban areas in the region.
parallels the blackstone river, known for its historic mills and canals, and serves as a main artery for local traffic between the two cities.
serves as a shortcut around heavily congested areas, providing rapid access to shopping centers and beaches.
travels through a series of historical sites linked to traditional crafts and industries, featuring old mills, lighthouses, and maritime museums.
links agricultural areas to suburban centers, providing vital access for local produce and goods trade.
travels along the coast, providing access to historical landmarks related to early american colonial settlements, including the famous pilgrim monument.
acts as a rapid link between burgeoning tech hubs in the region, supporting both local and commuter traffic.

johnny finds a mysterious lady named lady dorma and takes her back to the headquarters. she claims to have come from a land beneath the sea called pacifica, which is under siege by attuma. they manage to slip past attuma’s forces. pacifica is losing hope and attuma has shadowed the seabed. triton can only fight man-to-man with attuma while his men prepare traps to weaken triton into a losing battle. the fantastic 4 thwart every trap. triton beats attuma and the forces retreat. note: due to the rights to the sub-mariner being held by grantray-lawrence animation, the adaptation of the first meeting between the ff and namor was altered. instead, prince triton, an original pastiche of namor was reworked into the namor role.

the mole man is creating earthquakes and causing buildings to sink deep into the earth. in addition, he and his moloids kidnap susan. the mole man as usual has been expecting the other three and sends them back to the surface to tell the army not to get involved. they manage to halt them and seek an alternate entrance in the underworld. johnny rescues susan, then they penetrate the laboratory. they all return the buildings to the surface and escape the exploding caves.

after coming back from vacation reed tells ben an interesting theory on attempting to restore him. they head to dr. doom’s deserted castle to use the time machine the doctor left behind. in 2000 b.c the four weaken during a fight and are taken by pharaoh rama-tut, who is a lot more than he would seem at first sight. susan is to be rama-tut’s queen while the other three are put to work with some mind control. ben turns back to his former self. as he rescues susan, he is once again the thing. the four battle rama-tut to his sphinx. finally, they destroy his sphinx and return to their own time.

the watcher has made strange events in hope of preventing the silver surfer from coming but the plan fails and the surfer summons galactus. susan assists the unconscious surfer and he begins to think differently. the watcher has a plan only johnny can undergo. reed and ben sabotage galactus' earth draining machine and the silver surfer arrives to battle galactus. this angers galactus, but johnny gets back with the weapon that makes galactus see reason not to destroy the earth. note: in the episode "galactus", susan richards (the invisible girl) has the role originated by alicia masters (explaining to the silver surfer about humanity).
the micro world of dr. doom

the fantastic four have been shrunken to small size. dr. doom is after them and takes them to the micro world. dr. doom briefs them on his micro genius experiments involving a king and a princess from the micro world. the four battle the giant guards but dr. doom catches them and imprisons them with the king and princess. they all escape and enlarge themselves. ben puts a stop to the lizard men, then the four return to their own world.

on a remote planet, its inhabitants are fighting against blastaar and are able to banish him. reed and johnny enter the dangerous space zone via dimensional transport. as they depart, blastaar escapes and follows them. blastaar is too powerful for the four to handle. they lure blastaar into an evacuated atomic power plant, where they use some atomic matter to put him in a coma. they eject him through the dimensional transport back into the space zone.

the fantastic four study a radiated meteor. the molecule man appears and threatens the public. after the fantastic four tastes some of his power, he leaves to undergo his ruling the world. reed has developed a weapon he thinks will defeat the molecule man. the weapon works, but the molecule man gets away. the fantastic four continue their pursuit. the plan to stop the molecule man is tricky. they manage to reverse the molecule man’s form with a fragment of the meteor.

the fantastic four are taken to another planet where they are regarded as criminals against evil, charged by three old enemies. reed is forced to recall his memories on klaw, molecule, man and blastaar’s defeat. meanwhile the other three escape and they rescue reed just as the verdict is given. at the surface, they have to battle the court judge before they are able to leave the planet for earth.

the imposter plans to lure the fantastic four into a trap by posing as a famous hollywood director. the four are tempted to be in a movie and briefly retell their previous adventures to the director. the next day, the four fly to the director’s island and the director blows them out of the sky. the fantastic four are forced to go through the director’s deadly movie landscapes and make it to the boat on the other side of the island which the director detonates. the imposter removes his disguise and the fantastic four surprise him. the real director prevents the imposter from escaping upon forgetting that he had locked the director in the room that imposter was escaping into. the fantastic four have no desire to be movie stars in the end.

the fantastic four embark on a journey to the negative zone after discovering an unstable rift connected to it. they unknowingly open a portal, releasing the conquering anihilus. with his cosmic control rod, anihilus begins to alter the earth's gravitational field. the fantastic four construct a device to contain anihilus and force him back to the negative zone. with triumph, they seal the portal and restore balance to earth's gravity.

the fantastic four encounter a distress signal from a distant planet threatened by the power-hungry villain, quasar. on arriving, they discover quasar draining the planet’s energy to increase his power. after a strategic battle, the fantastic four manage to turn quasar’s device against him, restoring the planet's energy and forcing him to relinquish his control. they build a bond with the planet's inhabitants before returning home.

an ancient artifact containing the captive essence of the phantom force is discovered by ben at an archaeological dig. once released, the phantom force begins to possess and manipulate matter around them. the fantastic four devise a plan using their combined strengths to trap the phantom force back within a newly devised energy prison, shielding it from ever being released again.

while experimenting with an alien substance, reed inadvertently triggers a symbiotic alien invasion. ben is the first to be overtaken, turning against his friends. eventually, the fantastic four find a frequency that disrupts the symbiotic connection, freeing ben and defeating the horde. they secure the substance in a containment unit, sending it to the ends of the universe.

summoned by the watcher, the fantastic four must intervene in a cosmic trial determining the fate of an advanced alien race. accused of meddling with universal laws, this race faces annihilation. through diplomacy and evidence of their own experiences, the fantastic four sway the jury of watchers, allowing the aliens a chance at redemption.

doctor doom returns with an ancient celestial artifact, the zodiac array, granting him dominion over the astrological elements. darkness enshrouds new york as doom's power rises. in a climactic showdown, the fantastic four engage doom in a tactical battle, utilizing the cosmic rays that empower them to destabilize and dismantle the zodiac array, saving the city from doom’s tyranny.

the alignment of planets has caused disturbances in worldwide electromagnetic fields. ancient markers indicate this could awaken a galactic entity known as the arbiter. the fantastic four race against time to decipher the markers and prevent the arbiter’s awakening. through collaboration, they manage to alter the alignment using a reflective satellite, averting catastrophe.

mysterious shadow creatures begin appearing, preying on the fears and weaknesses of humanity. with no tangible form to combat, the fantastic four are at a loss until susan discovers the creatures are weak to light. with this knowledge, the team constructs light amplifying devices, dispelling the shadow menace looming over the earth.

the fabric between dimensions starts to tear, creating vortexes that merge realities. a council from alternate earths warns that failure to repair the fabric could mean universal collapse. the fantastic four, using their scientific prowess, work to mend the rift, collaborating with their alternate selves. together, they stabilize the dimensions, securing reality as they know it.

contacted by a cosmic league of peacekeepers, the fantastic four embarks on a journey beyond the stars to thwart a mighty empire threatening universal order. using their unique abilities and ingenuity, the team navigates political landscapes and battles, forging new alliances. their victory solidifies their status as not just earth’s defenders, but as guardians of the galaxy.

statement: which episode features the return of dr. doom?
table_text: the fantastic four are off to carry out their experiments on a remote island. the mole man, however, has been waiting for them and traps them in a radiation field and plans to submerge the world’s largest cities. the fantastic four escape but the mole man traps them again. they manage to escape their separate ways. they foil mole man’s domination and escape the island once and for all.

the fantastic four find a ruined castle in the middle of a forest in transylvania. ben is summoned by diablo and unable to resist, opens diablo's prison, unleashing him and later brainwashing ben. diablo tricks the world into thinking he has the power to help them. the world then realises what a fraud diablo really is. the fantastic four seize this opportunity to attack diablo’s castle. after getting far in the dungeons, the four get captured. ben escapes, releases the others and they defeat diablo.

while on a television show, reed recalls the time he first met victor von doom before he became dr. doom. he had ben as his roommate at university. victor was working on dangerous experiments, especially a test that brought him to the hospital and got him expelled from university. worse than that, the test altered his face and he swore revenge on reed having to hide his work from him. ben and reed became soldiers in world war ii. ben, susan, johnny and reed all went aboard a space rocket for space exploration. and so the origin of the fantastic four began. dr. doom confronts the fantastic four on the television show and briefs them on his origin. after that dr. doom attempts to get his revenge, but fails and escapes only to crash.

the skrulls have immediately failed to destroy the fantastic four. they introduce the super-skrull who possesses double power effects the fantastic four have. the fantastic four are overwhelmed by the super-skrull’s combined powers. the fantastic four lure the super-skrull to crater island. susan plants a sonic wave jamming device on the super-skrull before he can destroy them with his ultimate power level.
klaw is here to vanquish the fantastic 4 with his solidifying sonic waves. johnny is on vacation or so it would seem and arrives in the nick of time to assist mr. fantastic in catching the klaw.

reed is competing with dr. kragoff in race to the moon for astronomical research. during the launch, dr. kragoff and his primate crew have developed some reverse energy powers. dr. kragoff is now transparent and becomes the red ghost. red ghost kidnaps susan after counter attacking. she escapes and thwarts red ghost’s attempt to eliminate her companions. using a special device, reed turns red ghost into a plastic statue.

a ufo has been sighted. the pilot abducts the fantastic four from the science center and is setting course for planet x. there, their dictator kurrgo requests the fantastic four save their planet from another planet knocked off its orbit. reed manages to formulate a working plan to save the population. while the plan is in process, kurrgo has other ideas. however, reed tricks kurrgo and leaves him on the exploding planet while the micro-sized population and the fantastic four get away to safety.

the fantastic four face a bunch of old rivals in yancy street, but their old enemy red ghost and his primates show up and capture them. during their voyage to the moon, the four turn the tables, but red ghost gets away and the four are dumped on the moon. they barely manage to get to a source of oxygen which is the watcher’s laboratory. using one of the watcher’s machines, reed brings down red ghost’s ship. susan gets dr. kragoff banished into a trans-nitron machine. reed uses that machine to get back to earth.

the fantastic four face a new team called the frightful four. this team consists of the wizard, medusa, paste-pot pete, and the sandman. they capture the fantastic four, but johnny manages to alert the rest of the team and they defeat the frightful four.

dr. doom is back and he has a new plan to swap bodies with reed richards. dr. doom's plan initially succeeds, causing havoc among the fantastic four as they try to cope with reed being in doom's body. eventually, reed outsmarts dr. doom and the fantastic four manage to trap doom back in his own body.

the fantastic four encounter a new enemy who manipulates reality using a powerful artifact known as the yin-yang crystal. the team is split between two alternate realities and must find a way to unite and destroy the crystal before it causes permanent chaos.

a mysterious threat is causing panic across major cities, and the fantastic four discover an invisible alien race planning an invasion. using a special visibility serum developed by reed, the team manages to expose the alien fleet and thwart their invasion plans.

the fantastic four travel to egypt to investigate strange occurrences at the pyramids. they uncover an ancient curse linked to a powerful alien device hidden inside the sphinx. with the help of local archaeologists, the team neutralizes the device and prevents an impending cataclysm.

a cosmic signal draws the fantastic four into space where they encounter a nearly omnipotent being who is testing civilizations on their worthiness to continue. the team must prove humanity's potential without resorting to violence or destruction.

the fantastic four investigate a haunted hotel where guests have been vanishing at an alarming rate. it turns out to be the work of an old foe using hologram technology and illusions to scare guests away from discovering a hidden treasure.

a meteor lands on earth and starts to affect the natural elements, causing storms, volcanic eruptions, and earthquakes. the fantastic four discover that the meteor is a beacon for elemental beings and must find a way to deactivate it before the planet is consumed.

statement: which location has the longest route listed in the table?
table_text: runs from concord avenue to the mystic valley parkway.
runs through tiverton, rhode island; fall river, massachusetts; westport, massachusetts

route 24 is a connector between the fall river/new bedford area east of rhode island to the boston metropolitan area, connecting the major freeways of the area: i-195 in fall river and i-93/us-1 near i-95 in randolph.\n- route 79 runs along the highway between exits 7 and 9, concurrent with route 24.\n- i-195 has a brief concurrency with route 24 in fall river.
most of us-20 between marlborough and weston runs along the boston post road.
freeway comprises the eastern 5 miles (8.0 km) of route 57, connecting route 187 to u.s. route 5 and i-91.

route 9 between worcester and boston is mostly a divided full-access highway with traffic light-controlled intersections which serves as one of the main alternatives to the massachusetts turnpike. many shopping centers, car dealers, full-service restaurants and businesses line the roadway on this stretch, especially in framingham, such as barnes & noble, marshalls, t.g.i. fridays, kohl's, toys "r" us, best buy, olive garden and walmart. this stretch of the roadway is also encompassed in the golden triangle district of massachusetts.

the central artery is the portion of i-93 in downtown boston, which runs from massachusetts ave. (just south of exit 20) north to u.s. route 1's departure at exit 27.\nroute 3 leaves the artery at exit 26.
stretches from weston/newton line to the boston public garden.

the east boston expressway comprises the first 1.2 miles (1.9 km) of route 1a's northern segment. it stretches from i-93 exit 24 at the southern end of the callahan tunnel (northbound) and the sumner tunnel (southbound) to just northeast of the interchange with route 145 in east boston, near the eastern end of the mass pike.
grand army of the republic highway
the cross-country u.s. route 6 is designated grand army of the republic highway over its entire length, which spans 3,205 miles (5,158 km).
route 88 serves as a connector running from the horseneck beach reservation north to i-195 exit 10 in westport.
route 213 is designated "loop connector." it serves as a freeway connection between interstates 93 and 495 in methuen.
route 146a in massachusetts is designated as the lydia taft highway, which runs from the rhode island state border to route 122 in uxbridge.

the mass pike is a toll road running from the new york state border to downtown boston. it serves as the main cross-state freeway connecting the western and eastern portions of the state. the "pike" carries the easternmost 138 miles (222 km) of cross-country interstate 90.

u.s. route 3 and ma route 3 connect to each other on memorial drive, which runs from the fresh pond parkway to main street.\nroute 2 travels along memorial drive with us-3 and leaves via the boston university bridge.
the mid-cape highway is the main highway on cape cod, a 36-mile (58 km) long freeway running from route 3 and the sagamore bridge east to the orleans rotary.
the 65-mile (105 km) mohawk trail comprises the western section of route 2, from the new york border east to orange, and is regarded as one of the most scenic drives in the area.
runs from the alewife brook parkway to the revere beach parkway.

this section of u.s. route 1 runs from i-93 exit 27 (tobin bridge) to an interchange with route 60 in revere. this was originally supposed to be part of i-95, but i-95 was cancelled in boston, with i-93 and us-1 taking its place.
the northwest expressway serves as a freeway connection between i-95/route 128 (exit 32a) in burlington and the f.e. everett turnpike in nashua, nh.

the pilgrims highway is the southern portion of route 3, a 42-mile (68 km) long freeway which serves as a connector between cape cod (via u.s. route 6) and the boston metropolitan area (via i-93 and i-95).\n- u.s. route 44 runs along the highway between exits 6 and 7.
the southeast expressway is the section of i-93 between the route 3 split (exit 7) and the mass ave. interchange (exit 18), where it continues into boston as the central artery.
the southern artery is a major arterial in the city of quincy, running from quincy ave to the furnace brook parkway.
taunton-new bedford expressway\n(alfred m. bessette memorial highway)
the new bedford expressway comprises the southern 19 miles (31 km) of route 140, and serves as a freeway connection between u.s. route 6 in new bedford and route 24 (exit 12) in taunton, near i-495.
route 9 in framingham is named the ted williams highway, in commemoration of late boston red sox hall-of-famer ted williams who wore the number 9 on his jersey.
i-84 in massachusetts is designated the wilbur cross highway. it runs 8 miles (13 km) from the connecticut state border to the mass pike at exit 9.

route 146 is a freeway that, along with rhode island's route 146, serves to connect the metropolitan areas of providence and worcester. the entire route starts from i-95 in providence, with the massachusetts section picking up at the state line in millville. the highway runs 21 miles (34 km) northward, intersecting the mass pike (i-90) in worcester, and terminating at i-290 shortly thereafter.\n- route 122a runs along the highway between exits 9 and 12, concurrently with route 146.

the yankee division highway consists of the route 128 beltway before it was truncated to its southern terminus in canton, and continues to span its entire length. it stretches from i-93's exit 7 in braintree to route 128's northern terminus at route 127a in gloucester.
- i-95 runs along the highway between exits 12 and 45 (concurrent with 128).
- i-93 runs along the highway between exits 1 and 7.
- u.s. route 1 runs along the highway between i-95 exit 15b and i-93 exit 7.
connects the charlestown neighborhood to the sullivan square rotary, serving as a crucial link for local traffic.
one of the major traffic circles near the downtown area, facilitating the interchange of several routes.
runs parallel to route 24, providing local access to residential areas between the two towns.
links the intersection of i-93 and route 28 with the blue hills reservation, offering access to scenic landmarks.
runs along the charles river, connecting soldiers field in allston with the central artery through a scenic drive.
a connector between route 2 and route 62, spanning forested and residential areas in the two towns.
functions as a key thoroughfare from new york state to the massachusetts turnpike, enabling regional travel and transport.
winds through scenic landscapes, linking route 138 with historic town centers and recreational areas.
serves as an alternate route along the canal, providing important local access between these cape cod towns.
offers a key rural route that parallels the connecticut river, bridging two vibrant agricultural communities.
links route 109 with route 495, easing congestion for local commuters and expanding access to regional highways.

johnny finds a mysterious lady named lady dorma and takes her back to the headquarters. she claims to have come from a land beneath the sea called pacifica, which is under siege by attuma. they manage to slip past attuma’s forces. pacifica is losing hope and attuma has shadowed the seabed. triton can only fight man-to-man with attuma while his men prepare traps to weaken triton into a losing battle. the fantastic 4 thwart every trap. triton beats attuma and the forces retreat. note: due to the rights to the sub-mariner being held by grantray-lawrence animation, the adaptation of the first meeting between the ff and namor was altered. instead, prince triton, an original pastiche of namor was reworked into the namor role.

the mole man is creating earthquakes and causing buildings to sink deep into the earth. in addition, he and his moloids kidnap susan. the mole man as usual has been expecting the other three and sends them back to the surface to tell the army not to get involved. they manage to halt them and seek an alternate entrance in the underworld. johnny rescues susan, then they penetrate the laboratory. they all return the buildings to the surface and escape the exploding caves.

after coming back from vacation reed tells ben an interesting theory on attempting to restore him. they head to dr. doom’s deserted castle to use the time machine the doctor left behind. in 2000 b.c the four weaken during a fight and are taken by pharaoh rama-tut, who is a lot more than he would seem at first sight. susan is to be rama-tut’s queen while the other three are put to work with some mind control. ben turns back to his former self. as he rescues susan, he is once again the thing. the four battle rama-tut to his sphinx. finally, they destroy his sphinx and return to their own time.

the watcher has made strange events in hope of preventing the silver surfer from coming but the plan fails and the surfer summons galactus. susan assists the unconscious surfer and he begins to think differently. the watcher has a plan only johnny can undergo. reed and ben sabotage galactus' earth draining machine and the silver surfer arrives to battle galactus. this angers galactus, but johnny gets back with the weapon that makes galactus see reason not to destroy the earth. note: in the episode "galactus", susan richards (the invisible girl) has the role originated by alicia masters (explaining to the silver surfer about humanity).
the micro world of dr. doom

the fantastic four have been shrunken to small size. dr. doom is after them and takes them to the micro world. dr. doom briefs them on his micro genius experiments involving a king and a princess from the micro world. the four battle the giant guards but dr. doom catches them and imprisons them with the king and princess. they all escape and enlarge themselves. ben puts a stop to the lizard men, then the four return to their own world.

on a remote planet, its inhabitants are fighting against blastaar and are able to banish him. reed and johnny enter the dangerous space zone via dimensional transport. as they depart, blastaar escapes and follows them. blastaar is too powerful for the four to handle. they lure blastaar into an evacuated atomic power plant, where they use some atomic matter to put him in a coma. they eject him through the dimensional transport back into the space zone.

the fantastic four study a radiated meteor. the molecule man appears and threatens the public. after the fantastic four tastes some of his power, he leaves to undergo his ruling the world. reed has developed a weapon he thinks will defeat the molecule man. the weapon works, but the molecule man gets away. the fantastic four continue their pursuit. the plan to stop the molecule man is tricky. they manage to reverse the molecule man’s form with a fragment of the meteor.

the fantastic four are taken to another planet where they are regarded as criminals against evil, charged by three old enemies. reed is forced to recall his memories on klaw, molecule, man and blastaar’s defeat. meanwhile the other three escape and they rescue reed just as the verdict is given. at the surface, they have to battle the court judge before they are able to leave the planet for earth.

the imposter plans to lure the fantastic four into a trap by posing as a famous hollywood director. the four are tempted to be in a movie and briefly retell their previous adventures to the director. the next day, the four fly to the director’s island and the director blows them out of the sky. the fantastic four are forced to go through the director’s deadly movie landscapes and make it to the boat on the other side of the island which the director detonates. the imposter removes his disguise and the fantastic four surprise him. the real director prevents the imposter from escaping upon forgetting that he had locked the director in the room that imposter was escaping into. the fantastic four have no desire to be movie stars in the end.

the fantastic four encounter an alien race that appeared as shadowy figures. these beings possess the power to create illusions and intend to enslave humanity. reed devises a gadget to dispel their illusions, allowing the team to confront and defeat the aliens, who retreat back to their own dimension.

the fantastic four are trapped in the negative zone, a parallel universe full of dangers. here, they face an old adversary, anihilus, who seeks to use them for his sinister plans. the team must use their wits and strengths to return to their dimension and thwart anihilus's plans.

the krees, an advanced alien race, have come to earth with the intention of conquering it. the fantastic four must convince them that earth is not a threat and fight against their powerful technology to save humanity.

the fantastic four are trapped in an intricate labyrinth created by a genius named the master. each section of the maze tests their powers and intellect. working together, they outsmart the master and dismantle the labyrinth.

a powerful wizard summons the silver serpent to rule over the mystical and human realms. the fantastic four join forces with the sorcerer supreme to thwart the wizard's plans and send the serpent back to its mystical prison.

a trio of villains with unique elemental powers form the red triad and aim to destroy the fantastic four to prove their supremacy. the team counters each of the villains' powers through clever teamwork and ultimately defeats them.

the fantastic four face prince nalor, a water warlord from the depths of the sea who seeks vengeance on the surface world. susan discovers a way to communicate with him, revealing misunderstandings. peace is made and nalor returns to the ocean.
a time traveler known as the phantom attempts to change the course of history to suit his vision. the fantastic four chase him across time, undoing the changes and preserving the timeline.

the fantastic four journey into the heart of the desert to investigate mysterious sandstorms. they discover an ancient alien artifact controlling the elements. they work together to disable the device, restoring peace to the land.

the team finds themselves in a crystalline city where a rogue scientist uses mind-control technology on the inhabitants. the fantastic four must navigate the city's challenges to free its people and stop the scientist.

statement: which highway is part of route 146 and connects providence to worcester?

runs through tiverton, rhode island; fall river, massachusetts; westport, massachusetts

route 24 is a connector between the fall river/new bedford area east of rhode island to the boston metropolitan area, connecting the major freeways of the area: i-195 in fall river and i-93/us-1 near i-95 in randolph.\n- route 79 runs along the highway between exits 7 and 9, concurrent with route 24.\n- i-195 has a brief concurrency with route 24 in fall river.
most of us-20 between marlborough and weston runs along the boston post road.
freeway comprises the eastern 5 miles (8.0 km) of route 57, connecting route 187 to u.s. route 5 and i-91.

route 9 between worcester and boston is mostly a divided full-access highway with traffic light-controlled intersections which serves as one of the main alternatives to the massachusetts turnpike. many shopping centers, car dealers, full-service restaurants and businesses line the roadway on this stretch, especially in framingham, such as barnes & noble, marshalls, t.g.i. fridays, kohl's, toys "r" us, best buy, olive garden and walmart. this stretch of the roadway is also encompassed in the golden triangle district of massachusetts.

the central artery is the portion of i-93 in downtown boston, which runs from massachusetts ave. (just south of exit 20) north to u.s. route 1's departure at exit 27.\nroute 3 leaves the artery at exit 26.
stretches from weston/newton line to the boston public garden.

the east boston expressway comprises the first 1.2 miles (1.9 km) of route 1a's northern segment. it stretches from i-93 exit 24 at the southern end of the callahan tunnel (northbound) and the sumner tunnel (southbound) to just northeast of the interchange with route 145 in east boston, near the eastern end of the mass pike.
grand army of the republic highway
the cross-country u.s. route 6 is designated grand army of the republic highway over its entire length, which spans 3,205 miles (5,158 km).
route 88 serves as a connector running from the horseneck beach reservation north to i-195 exit 10 in westport.
route 213 is designated "loop connector." it serves as a freeway connection between interstates 93 and 495 in methuen.
route 146a in massachusetts is designated as the lydia taft highway, which runs from the rhode island state border to route 122 in uxbridge.

the mass pike is a toll road running from the new york state border to downtown boston. it serves as the main cross-state freeway connecting the western and eastern portions of the state. the "pike" carries the easternmost 138 miles (222 km) of cross-country interstate 90.

u.s. route 3 and ma route 3 connect to each other on memorial drive, which runs from the fresh pond parkway to main street.\nroute 2 travels along memorial drive with us-3 and leaves via the boston university bridge.
the mid-cape highway is the main highway on cape cod, a 36-mile (58 km) long freeway running from route 3 and the sagamore bridge east to the orleans rotary.
the 65-mile (105 km) mohawk trail comprises the western section of route 2, from the new york border east to orange, and is regarded as one of the most scenic drives in the area.
runs from the alewife brook parkway to the revere beach parkway.

this section of u.s. route 1 runs from i-93 exit 27 (tobin bridge) to an interchange with route 60 in revere. this was originally supposed to be part of i-95, but i-95 was cancelled in boston, with i-93 and us-1 taking its place.
the northwest expressway serves as a freeway connection between i-95/route 128 (exit 32a) in burlington and the f.e. everett turnpike in nashua, nh.

the pilgrims highway is the southern portion of route 3, a 42-mile (68 km) long freeway which serves as a connector between cape cod (via u.s. route 6) and the boston metropolitan area (via i-93 and i-95).\n- u.s. route 44 runs along the highway between exits 6 and 7.
the southeast expressway is the section of i-93 between the route 3 split (exit 7) and the mass ave. interchange (exit 18), where it continues into boston as the central artery.
the southern artery is a major arterial in the city of quincy, running from quincy ave to the furnace brook parkway.
taunton-new bedford expressway\n(alfred m. bessette memorial highway)
the new bedford expressway comprises the southern 19 miles (31 km) of route 140, and serves as a freeway connection between u.s. route 6 in new bedford and route 24 (exit 12) in taunton, near i-495.
route 9 in framingham is named the ted williams highway, in commemoration of late boston red sox hall-of-famer ted williams who wore the number 9 on his jersey.
i-84 in massachusetts is designated the wilbur cross highway. it runs 8 miles (13 km) from the connecticut state border to the mass pike at exit 9.

route 146 is a freeway that, along with rhode island's route 146, serves to connect the metropolitan areas of providence and worcester. the entire route starts from i-95 in providence, with the massachusetts section picking up at the state line in millville. the highway runs 21 miles (34 km) northward, intersecting the mass pike (i-90) in worcester, and terminating at i-290 shortly thereafter.\n- route 122a runs along the highway between exits 9 and 12, concurrently with route 146.

the yankee division highway consists of the route 128 beltway before it was truncated to its southern terminus in canton, and continues to span its entire length. it stretches from i-93's exit 7 in braintree to route 128's northern terminus at route 127a in gloucester.

- i-93 runs along the highway between exits 1 and 7.
- u.s. route 1 runs along the highway between i-95 exit 15b and i-93 exit 7.
route 58 runs along axel weymouth highway from route 106 in halifax to route 18 in weymouth.
vineyard view expressway is a scenic route running from the cape cod canal to woods hole, showcasing views of martha's vineyard.
the parkway runs from main street in springfield along the connecticut river, providing access to local parks and recreation areas.
road that traces the historic route of the first armed conflict of the american revolution, offering access to many historic sites.
a steep, winding road leading to the summit of cloudy peak, popular with hikers and cyclists.
roads in the area trace the historic routes once used to transport logs to paper mills, now a scenic byway.
runs from saugus to the revere junction, it's lined with various monuments commemorating the early industrial era in the area.
a quiet, scenic road passing through expansive meadows and farmland in the outskirts of andover.

statement: how long is the yankee division highway?
table_text: runs from concord avenue to the mystic valley parkway.
runs through tiverton, rhode island; fall river, massachusetts; westport, massachusetts

route 24 is a connector between the fall river/new bedford area east of rhode island to the boston metropolitan area, connecting the major freeways of the area: i-195 in fall river and i-93/us-1 near i-95 in randolph.\n- route 79 runs along the highway between exits 7 and 9, concurrent with route 24.\n- i-195 has a brief concurrency with route 24 in fall river.
most of us-20 between marlborough and weston runs along the boston post road.
freeway comprises the eastern 5 miles (8.0 km) of route 57, connecting route 187 to u.s. route 5 and i-91.

route 9 between worcester and boston is mostly a divided full-access highway with traffic light-controlled intersections which serves as one of the main alternatives to the massachusetts turnpike. many shopping centers, car dealers, full-service restaurants and businesses line the roadway on this stretch, especially in framingham, such as barnes & noble, marshalls, t.g.i. fridays, kohl's, toys "r" us, best buy, olive garden and walmart. this stretch of the roadway is also encompassed in the golden triangle district of massachusetts.

the central artery is the portion of i-93 in downtown boston, which runs from massachusetts ave. (just south of exit 20) north to u.s. route 1's departure at exit 27.\nroute 3 leaves the artery at exit 26.
stretches from weston/newton line to the boston public garden.

the east boston expressway comprises the first 1.2 miles (1.9 km) of route 1a's northern segment. it stretches from i-93 exit 24 at the southern end of the callahan tunnel (northbound) and the sumner tunnel (southbound) to just northeast of the interchange with route 145 in east boston, near the eastern end of the mass pike.
grand army of the republic highway
the cross-country u.s. route 6 is designated grand army of the republic highway over its entire length, which spans 3,205 miles (5,158 km).
route 88 serves as a connector running from the horseneck beach reservation north to i-195 exit 10 in westport.
route 213 is designated "loop connector." it serves as a freeway connection between interstates 93 and 495 in methuen.
route 146a in massachusetts is designated as the lydia taft highway, which runs from the rhode island state border to route 122 in uxbridge.

the mass pike is a toll road running from the new york state border to downtown boston. it serves as the main cross-state freeway connecting the western and eastern portions of the state. the "pike" carries the easternmost 138 miles (222 km) of cross-country interstate 90.

u.s. route 3 and ma route 3 connect to each other on memorial drive, which runs from the fresh pond parkway to main street.\nroute 2 travels along memorial drive with us-3 and leaves via the boston university bridge.
the mid-cape highway is the main highway on cape cod, a 36-mile (58 km) long freeway running from route 3 and the sagamore bridge east to the orleans rotary.
the 65-mile (105 km) mohawk trail comprises the western section of route 2, from the new york border east to orange, and is regarded as one of the most scenic drives in the area.
runs from the alewife brook parkway to the revere beach parkway.

this section of u.s. route 1 runs from i-93 exit 27 (tobin bridge) to an interchange with route 60 in revere. this was originally supposed to be part of i-95, but i-95 was cancelled in boston, with i-93 and us-1 taking its place.
the northwest expressway serves as a freeway connection between i-95/route 128 (exit 32a) in burlington and the f.e. everett turnpike in nashua, nh.

the pilgrims highway is the southern portion of route 3, a 42-mile (68 km) long freeway which serves as a connector between cape cod (via u.s. route 6) and the boston metropolitan area (via i-93 and i-95).\n- u.s. route 44 runs along the highway between exits 6 and 7.
the southeast expressway is the section of i-93 between the route 3 split (exit 7) and the mass ave. interchange (exit 18), where it continues into boston as the central artery.
the southern artery is a major arterial in the city of quincy, running from quincy ave to the furnace brook parkway.
taunton-new bedford expressway\n(alfred m. bessette memorial highway)
the new bedford expressway comprises the southern 19 miles (31 km) of route 140, and serves as a freeway connection between u.s. route 6 in new bedford and route 24 (exit 12) in taunton, near i-495.
route 9 in framingham is named the ted williams highway, in commemoration of late boston red sox hall-of-famer ted williams who wore the number 9 on his jersey.
i-84 in massachusetts is designated the wilbur cross highway. it runs 8 miles (13 km) from the connecticut state border to the mass pike at exit 9.

route 146 is a freeway that, along with rhode island's route 146, serves to connect the metropolitan areas of providence and worcester. the entire route starts from i-95 in providence, with the massachusetts section picking up at the state line in millville. the highway runs 21 miles (34 km) northward, intersecting the mass pike (i-90) in worcester, and terminating at i-290 shortly thereafter.\n- route 122a runs along the highway between exits 9 and 12, concurrently with route 146.

the yankee division highway consists of the route 128 beltway before it was truncated to its southern terminus in canton, and continues to span its entire length. it stretches from i-93's exit 7 in braintree to route 128's northern terminus at route 127a in gloucester.
- i-95 runs along the highway between exits 12 and 45 (concurrent with 128).
- i-93 runs along the highway between exits 1 and 7.
- u.s. route 1 runs along the highway between i-95 exit 15b and i-93 exit 7.
hancock street is a main arterial road running north-south from quincy center to wollaston beaches.
passes through the waterfront district connecting to several wharfs and major piers, also hosting several public facilities.
connects the town center with adjacent suburbs, primarily residential areas with commercial intersections.
this road stretches across multiple towns, intersecting with route 24 and i-495, commonly used for local access.
important link between harvard square and alewife brook parkway, passing through several educational institutions.
provides key linkages to the highland avenue, servicing residential neighborhoods and small businesses.
a scenic drive following the riverbank, connecting smaller communities and recreation areas along the way.
hugs the nearby lake providing access to local parks and leisure areas, predominantly recreational in function.
one of the major connectors between residential central massachusetts and commercial hubs towards eastern mass.
links the central business district with the historic waterfront area, known for seafood markets and shops.
directly leads to tufts university, intersects with route 16 bringing students and faculty traffic into the campus environment.

statement: which episode features the fantastic four being trapped by dr. doom in a micro world?
table_text: the fantastic four are off to carry out their experiments on a remote island. the mole man, however, has been waiting for them and traps them in a radiation field and plans to submerge the world’s largest cities. the fantastic four escape but the mole man traps them again. they manage to escape their separate ways. they foil mole man’s domination and escape the island once and for all.

the fantastic four find a ruined castle in the middle of a forest in transylvania. ben is summoned by diablo and unable to resist, opens diablo's prison, unleashing him and later brainwashing ben. diablo tricks the world into thinking he has the power to help them. the world then realises what a fraud diablo really is. the fantastic four seize this opportunity to attack diablo’s castle. after getting far in the dungeons, the four get captured. ben escapes, releases the others and they defeat diablo.

while on a television show, reed recalls the time he first met victor von doom before he became dr. doom. he had ben as his roommate at university. victor was working on dangerous experiments, especially a test that brought him to the hospital and got him expelled from university. worse than that, the test altered his face and he swore revenge on reed having to hide his work from him. ben and reed became soldiers in world war ii. ben, susan, johnny and reed all went aboard a space rocket for space exploration. and so the origin of the fantastic four began. dr. doom confronts the fantastic four on the television show and briefs them on his origin. after that dr. doom attempts to get his revenge, but fails and escapes only to crash.

the skrulls have immediately failed to destroy the fantastic four. they introduce the super-skrull who possesses double power effects the fantastic four have. the fantastic four are overwhelmed by the super-skrull’s combined powers. the fantastic four lure the super-skrull to crater island. susan plants a sonic wave jamming device on the super-skrull before he can destroy them with his ultimate power level.
klaw is here to vanquish the fantastic 4 with his solidifying sonic waves. johnny is on vacation or so it would seem and arrives in the nick of time to assist mr. fantastic in catching the klaw.

reed is competing with dr. kragoff in race to the moon for astronomical research. during the launch, dr. kragoff and his primate crew have developed some reverse energy powers. dr. kragoff is now transparent and becomes the red ghost. red ghost kidnaps susan after counter attacking. she escapes and thwarts red ghost’s attempt to eliminate her companions. using a special device, reed turns red ghost into a plastic statue.

a ufo has been sighted. the pilot abducts the fantastic four from the science center and is setting course for planet x. there, their dictator kurrgo requests the fantastic four save their planet from another planet knocked off its orbit. reed manages to formulate a working plan to save the population. while the plan is in process, kurrgo has other ideas. however, reed tricks kurrgo and leaves him on the exploding planet while the micro-sized population and the fantastic four get away to safety.

the fantastic four face a bunch of old rivals in yancy street, but their old enemy red ghost and his primates show up and capture them. during their voyage to the moon, the four turn the tables, but red ghost gets away and the four are dumped on the moon. they barely manage to get to a source of oxygen which is the watcher’s laboratory. using one of the watcher’s machines, reed brings down red ghost’s ship. susan gets dr. kragoff banished into a trans-nitron machine. reed uses that machine to get back to earth.

dr. doom challenges the fantastic four. doctor doom begins his plans by capturing susan. soon the fantastic four manage to locate and penetrate dr. doom’s flying fortress, but ben is turned back to his former self and the other three are trapped. ben turns himself back into the thing, releases the others and aborts dr. doom’s tidal waves. they chase dr. doom out and back to the flying fortress. after a struggle through the dangerous complex of the fortress, they abort dr. doom’s global destruction for good.

the fantastic four are testing their rocket when they are drawn into the skrull galaxy. after beating the first round of skrulls, the fantastic four weaken and are taken prisoner. the cruel skrull warlord morrat wishes to overthrow the skrull emperor. the warlord gives the fantastic four the option to assist them or die. reed tricks the warlord into getting him and his friends' powers fully charged. they defeat the warlord as the emperor arrives and he allows the fantastic 4 to go freely back to earth.

the fantastic four beat the criminal forces working for dr. gamma, and blow up the island with its secret weapons. while escaping, dr. gamma is infected by the radiation levels in the seabed and morphs into some creature. johnny is flustered with being moved around and quits from the fantastic four. in the town johnny goes to, there have been sightings of the gamma ray. johnny defeats the gamma ray by himself, but he comes back with the hideous giant sea monster giganto. johnny rejoins the fantastic four. ben succeeds in eliminating the sea monster. the gamma ray is defeated but not finished.

johnny finds a mysterious lady named lady dorma and takes her back to the headquarters. she claims to have come from a land beneath the sea called pacifica, which is under siege by attuma. they manage to slip past attuma’s forces. pacifica is losing hope and attuma has shadowed the seabed. triton can only fight man-to-man with attuma while his men prepare traps to weaken triton into a losing battle. the fantastic 4 thwart every trap. triton beats attuma and the forces retreat. note: due to the rights to the sub-mariner being held by grantray-lawrence animation, the adaptation of the first meeting between the ff and namor was altered. instead, prince triton, an original pastiche of namor was reworked into the namor role.

the mole man is creating earthquakes and causing buildings to sink deep into the earth. in addition, he and his moloids kidnap susan. the mole man as usual has been expecting the other three and sends them back to the surface to tell the army not to get involved. they manage to halt them and seek an alternate entrance in the underworld. johnny rescues susan, then they penetrate the laboratory. they all return the buildings to the surface and escape the exploding caves.

after coming back from vacation reed tells ben an interesting theory on attempting to restore him. they head to dr. doom’s deserted castle to use the time machine the doctor left behind. in 2000 b.c the four weaken during a fight and are taken by pharaoh rama-tut, who is a lot more than he would seem at first sight. susan is to be rama-tut’s queen while the other three are put to work with some mind control. ben turns back to his former self. as he rescues susan, he is once again the thing. the four battle rama-tut to his sphinx. finally, they destroy his sphinx and return to their own time.

the watcher has made strange events in hope of preventing the silver surfer from coming but the plan fails and the surfer summons galactus. susan assists the unconscious surfer and he begins to think differently. the watcher has a plan only johnny can undergo. reed and ben sabotage galactus' earth draining machine and the silver surfer arrives to battle galactus. this angers galactus, but johnny gets back with the weapon that makes galactus see reason not to destroy the earth. note: in the episode "galactus", susan richards (the invisible girl) has the role originated by alicia masters (explaining to the silver surfer about humanity).
the micro world of dr. doom

the fantastic four have been shrunken to small size. dr. doom is after them and takes them to the micro world. dr. doom briefs them on his micro genius experiments involving a king and a princess from the micro world. the four battle the giant guards but dr. doom catches them and imprisons them with the king and princess. they all escape and enlarge themselves. ben puts a stop to the lizard men, then the four return to their own world.

on a remote planet, its inhabitants are fighting against blastaar and are able to banish him. reed and johnny enter the dangerous space zone via dimensional transport. as they depart, blastaar escapes and follows them. blastaar is too powerful for the four to handle. they lure blastaar into an evacuated atomic power plant, where they use some atomic matter to put him in a coma. they eject him through the dimensional transport back into the space zone.

the fantastic four study a radiated meteor. the molecule man appears and threatens the public. after the fantastic four tastes some of his power, he leaves to undergo his ruling the world. reed has developed a weapon he thinks will defeat the molecule man. the weapon works, but the molecule man gets away. the fantastic four continue their pursuit. the plan to stop the molecule man is tricky. they manage to reverse the molecule man’s form with a fragment of the meteor.

the fantastic four are taken to another planet where they are regarded as criminals against evil, charged by three old enemies. reed is forced to recall his memories on klaw, molecule, man and blastaar’s defeat. meanwhile the other three escape and they rescue reed just as the verdict is given. at the surface, they have to battle the court judge before they are able to leave the planet for earth.

the imposter plans to lure the fantastic four into a trap by posing as a famous hollywood director. the four are tempted to be in a movie and briefly retell their previous adventures to the director. the next day, the four fly to the director’s island and the director blows them out of the sky. the fantastic four are forced to go through the director’s deadly movie landscapes and make it to the boat on the other side of the island which the director detonates. the imposter removes his disguise and the fantastic four surprise him. the real director prevents the imposter from escaping upon forgetting that he had locked the director in the room that imposter was escaping into. the fantastic four have no desire to be movie stars in the end.

the fantastic four investigate strange energy disruptions across the city. these disturbances lead them to a hidden underground facility run by the enigmatic villain named Aegis. Aegis harnesses the power of gemstones to generate massive energy surges. During their confrontation, the fantastic four must disable the energy conduits to prevent catastrophic city-wide blackouts. They manage to evade Aegis's traps and reverse the energy flow, thwarting his plans. Aegis escapes, vowing revenge.

dr. doom reappears with a device that allows him to manipulate time. the fantastic four must race against time to prevent dr. doom from altering history. reed devises a temporal stabilizer to counter dr. doom’s device. in a climactic showdown, they manage to trap dr. doom in a time loop, ensuring history remains unchanged.

a rogue scientist biomorph creates clones of the fantastic four with mirrored abilities. these clones wreak havoc, leaving the city in chaos. the real fantastic four confront their counterparts in a bid to restore their reputation. after intense battles, reed identifies the method to deactivate the clones, returning peace to the city.

while testing equipment in the arctic, the fantastic four battle an ancient ice elemental known as Kryos. its powers inadvertently release a prehistoric threat. combining their skills, they must seal the elemental back within the ice before the thaw unleashes a new ice age. a narrow victory leads them to reinforce the arctic barriers, protecting world climate stability.

a cosmic anomaly brings forth the nihilator, a villain capable of bending reality. the fantastic four find themselves trapped in distorted realms, struggling with twisted versions of themselves. as the nihilator’s grip strengthens, they focus their combined power on unraveling the reality warp, culminating in a surprising victory achieved through mental unity.
answer: the micro world of dr. doom
