statement: what episode features the fantastic four being trapped in a time loop?
table_text: the fantastic four are off to carry out their experiments on a remote island. the mole man, however, has been waiting for them and traps them in a radiation field and plans to submerge the world’s largest cities. the fantastic four escape but the mole man traps them again. they manage to escape their separate ways. they foil mole man’s domination and escape the island once and for all.

the fantastic four find a ruined castle in the middle of a forest in transylvania. ben is summoned by diablo and unable to resist, opens diablo's prison, unleashing him and later brainwashing ben. diablo tricks the world into thinking he has the power to help them. the world then realises what a fraud diablo really is. the fantastic four seize this opportunity to attack diablo’s castle. after getting far in the dungeons, the four get captured. ben escapes, releases the others and they defeat diablo.

while on a television show, reed recalls the time he first met victor von doom before he became dr. doom. he had ben as his roommate at university. victor was working on dangerous experiments, especially a test that brought him to the hospital and got him expelled from university. worse than that, the test altered his face and he swore revenge on reed having to hide his work from him. ben and reed became soldiers in world war ii. ben, susan, johnny and reed all went aboard a space rocket for space exploration. and so the origin of the fantastic four began. dr. doom confronts the fantastic four on the television show and briefs them on his origin. after that dr. doom attempts to get his revenge, but fails and escapes only to crash.

the skrulls have immediately failed to destroy the fantastic four. they introduce the super-skrull who possesses double power effects the fantastic four have. the fantastic four are overwhelmed by the super-skrull’s combined powers. the fantastic four lure the super-skrull to crater island. susan plants a sonic wave jamming device on the super-skrull before he can destroy them with his ultimate power level.
klaw is here to vanquish the fantastic 4 with his solidifying sonic waves. johnny is on vacation or so it would seem and arrives in the nick of time to assist mr. fantastic in catching the klaw.

reed is competing with dr. kragoff in race to the moon for astronomical research. during the launch, dr. kragoff and his primate crew have developed some reverse energy powers. dr. kragoff is now transparent and becomes the red ghost. red ghost kidnaps susan after counter attacking. she escapes and thwarts red ghost’s attempt to eliminate her companions. using a special device, reed turns red ghost into a plastic statue.

a ufo has been sighted. the pilot abducts the fantastic four from the science center and is setting course for planet x. there, their dictator kurrgo requests the fantastic four save their planet from another planet knocked off its orbit. reed manages to formulate a working plan to save the population. while the plan is in process, kurrgo has other ideas. however, reed tricks kurrgo and leaves him on the exploding planet while the micro-sized population and the fantastic four get away to safety.

the fantastic four face a bunch of old rivals in yancy street, but their old enemy red ghost and his primates show up and capture them. during their voyage to the moon, the four turn the tables, but red ghost gets away and the four are dumped on the moon. they barely manage to get to a source of oxygen which is the watcher’s laboratory. using one of the watcher’s machines, reed brings down red ghost’s ship. susan gets dr. kragoff banished into a trans-nitron machine. reed uses that machine to get back to earth.

dr. doom challenges the fantastic four. doctor doom begins his plans by capturing susan. soon the fantastic four manage to locate and penetrate dr. doom’s flying fortress, but ben is turned back to his former self and the other three are trapped. ben turns himself back into the thing, releases the others and aborts dr. doom’s tidal waves. they chase dr. doom out and back to the flying fortress. after a struggle through the dangerous complex of the fortress, they abort dr. doom’s global destruction for good.

the fantastic four are testing their rocket when they are drawn into the skrull galaxy. after beating the first round of skrulls, the fantastic four weaken and are taken prisoner. the cruel skrull warlord morrat wishes to overthrow the skrull emperor. the warlord gives the fantastic four the option to assist them or die. reed tricks the warlord into getting him and his friends' powers fully charged. they defeat the warlord as the emperor arrives and he allows the fantastic 4 to go freely back to earth.

the fantastic four beat the criminal forces working for dr. gamma, and blow up the island with its secret weapons. while escaping, dr. gamma is infected by the radiation levels in the seabed and morphs into some creature. johnny is flustered with being moved around and quits from the fantastic four. in the town johnny goes to, there have been sightings of the gamma ray. johnny defeats the gamma ray by himself, but he comes back with the hideous giant sea monster giganto. johnny rejoins the fantastic four. ben succeeds in eliminating the sea monster. the gamma ray is defeated but not finished.

johnny finds a mysterious lady named lady dorma and takes her back to the headquarters. she claims to have come from a land beneath the sea called pacifica, which is under siege by attuma. they manage to slip past attuma’s forces. pacifica is losing hope and attuma has shadowed the seabed. triton can only fight man-to-man with attuma while his men prepare traps to weaken triton into a losing battle. the fantastic 4 thwart every trap. triton beats attuma and the forces retreat. note: due to the rights to the sub-mariner being held by grantray-lawrence animation, the adaptation of the first meeting between the ff and namor was altered. instead, prince triton, an original pastiche of namor was reworked into the namor role.

the mole man is creating earthquakes and causing buildings to sink deep into the earth. in addition, he and his moloids kidnap susan. the mole man as usual has been expecting the other three and sends them back to the surface to tell the army not to get involved. they manage to halt them and seek an alternate entrance in the underworld. johnny rescues susan, then they penetrate the laboratory. they all return the buildings to the surface and escape the exploding caves.

after coming back from vacation reed tells ben an interesting theory on attempting to restore him. they head to dr. doom’s deserted castle to use the time machine the doctor left behind. in 2000 b.c the four weaken during a fight and are taken by pharaoh rama-tut, who is a lot more than he would seem at first sight. susan is to be rama-tut’s queen while the other three are put to work with some mind control. ben turns back to his former self. as he rescues susan, he is once again the thing. the four battle rama-tut to his sphinx. finally, they destroy his sphinx and return to their own time.

the imposter plans to lure the fantastic four into a trap by posing as a famous hollywood director. the four are tempted to be in a movie and briefly retell their previous adventures to the director. the next day, the four fly to the director’s island and the director blows them out of the sky. the fantastic four are forced to go through the director’s deadly movie landscapes and make it to the boat on the other side of the island which the director detonates. the imposter removes his disguise and the fantastic four surprise him. the real director prevents the imposter from escaping upon forgetting that he had locked the director in the room that imposter was escaping into. the fantastic four have no desire to be movie stars in the end.

the fantastic four are alerted by the presence of giant insectoids attacking the city. the insectoids originate from an underground world led by queen larva. while battling these creatures, the team discovers their weakness lies in intense light. they manage to repel the insects back to their domain by redirecting sunlight using a series of mirrors. queen larva retreats, vowing to return.

the fantastic four find themselves trapped in a time loop orchestrated by the timemaster, who seeks to erase them from existence. as they relive the same day repeatedly, reed devises a plan to outwit the time fluctuations. by harnessing cosmic rays, they manage to disrupt the loop and send the timemaster spiraling back into the void, restoring the timeline.

when a series of tidal waves threaten coastal cities, the fantastic four journey to atlantis. they discover that prince triton has been overthrown by the villainous hydron. with the help of atlantis' remaining loyalists, they defeat hydron and restore peace to the underwater realm, preventing further disaster on the surface.

the team encounters a mysterious crystal that amplifies their powers uncontrollably. dr. doom, having harnessed the crystal's energy, plans to control the fantastic four. through teamwork and strategy, they manage to shatter the crystal and foil doom's scheme, regaining control of their abilities.

the skrull have infiltrated earth once again, this time attempting to clone the fantastic four. the clones are unleashed upon the world, causing chaos. the team must battle their duplicates and find the skrulls' hidden base. by outsmarting the skrulls with their superior teamwork, they dismantle the cloning facility and return peace to the world.

the fantastic four embark on a mission to explore a newly discovered cavern emitting strange energies. inside, they face their darkest fears materialized by an ancient curse. reed identifies the source of the curse as an alien relic and disables it, returning the cavern to its original state and freeing the team from its eerie grasp.

the city is shaken by a series of unnatural earthquakes. the fantastic four discover that an aspiring villain, the quake master, is using a powerful device to create tremors. sneaking into his underground lair, they disable the machine just as it threatens to split the city apart, capturing quake master in the process.

elemental creatures begin terrorizing the city, each wielding control over a fundamental force of nature. the fantastic four deduce that these beings are connected to an ancient artifact unearthed during a construction project. by reversing the artifact's polarity, they are able to banish the creatures back to their own dimension.

a bizarre villain called the mirrorman has created an alternate universe within mirrors. the fantastic four find themselves trapped in this reflective world where physics operate differently. they cleverly manipulate reflections to find an escape, trapping the mirrorman within his own realm and restoring the balance between realities.

cosmic anomalies begin occurring worldwide, pulling objects into black holes. reed discovers that an alien entity is manipulating these black holes as part of a nefarious plan. the fantastic four fly into space, where they confront and contain the entity, closing the black holes and saving the earth from destruction.

which highways have an asterisk (*) for the route number(s)?
table_text: runs from concord avenue to the mystic valley parkway.
runs through tiverton, rhode island; fall river, massachusetts; westport, massachusetts

route 24 is a connector between the fall river/new bedford area east of rhode island to the boston metropolitan area, connecting the major freeways of the area: i-195 in fall river and i-93/us-1 near i-95 in randolph.\n- route 79 runs along the highway between exits 7 and 9, concurrent with route 24.\n- i-195 has a brief concurrency with route 24 in fall river.
most of us-20 between marlborough and weston runs along the boston post road.
freeway comprises the eastern 5 miles (8.0 km) of route 57, connecting route 187 to u.s. route 5 and i-91.

route 9 between worcester and boston is mostly a divided full-access highway with traffic light-controlled intersections which serves as one of the main alternatives to the massachusetts turnpike. many shopping centers, car dealers, full-service restaurants and businesses line the roadway on this stretch, especially in framingham, such as barnes & noble, marshalls, t.g.i. fridays, kohl's, toys "r" us, best buy, olive garden and walmart. this stretch of the roadway is also encompassed in the golden triangle district of massachusetts.

the central artery is the portion of i-93 in downtown boston, which runs from massachusetts ave. (just south of exit 20) north to u.s. route 1's departure at exit 27.\nroute 3 leaves the artery at exit 26.
stretches from weston/newton line to the boston public garden.

the east boston expressway comprises the first 1.2 miles (1.9 km) of route 1a's northern segment. it stretches from i-93 exit 24 at the southern end of the callahan tunnel (northbound) and the sumner tunnel (southbound) to just northeast of the interchange with route 145 in east boston, near the eastern end of the mass pike.
grand army of the republic highway
the cross-country u.s. route 6 is designated grand army of the republic highway over its entire length, which spans 3,205 miles (5,158 km).
route 88 serves as a connector running from the horseneck beach reservation north to i-195 exit 10 in westport.
route 213 is designated "loop connector." it serves as a freeway connection between interstates 93 and 495 in methuen.
route 146a in massachusetts is designated as the lydia taft highway, which runs from the rhode island state border to route 122 in uxbridge.

the mass pike is a toll road running from the new york state border to downtown boston. it serves as the main cross-state freeway connecting the western and eastern portions of the state. the "pike" carries the easternmost 138 miles (222 km) of cross-country interstate 90.

u.s. route 3 and ma route 3 connect to each other on memorial drive, which runs from the fresh pond parkway to main street.\nroute 2 travels along memorial drive with us-3 and leaves via the boston university bridge.
the mid-cape highway is the main highway on cape cod, a 36-mile (58 km) long freeway running from route 3 and the sagamore bridge east to the orleans rotary.
the 65-mile (105 km) mohawk trail comprises the western section of route 2, from the new york border east to orange, and is regarded as one of the most scenic drives in the area.
runs from the alewife brook parkway to the revere beach parkway.

this section of u.s. route 1 runs from i-93 exit 27 (tobin bridge) to an interchange with route 60 in revere. this was originally supposed to be part of i-95, but i-95 was cancelled in boston, with i-93 and us-1 taking its place.
the northwest expressway serves as a freeway connection between i-95/route 128 (exit 32a) in burlington and the f.e. everett turnpike in nashua, nh.

the pilgrims highway is the southern portion of route 3, a 42-mile (68 km) long freeway which serves as a connector between cape cod (via u.s. route 6) and the boston metropolitan area (via i-93 and i-95).\n- u.s. route 44 runs along the highway between exits 6 and 7.
the southeast expressway is the section of i-93 between the route 3 split (exit 7) and the mass ave. interchange (exit 18), where it continues into boston as the central artery.
the southern artery is a major arterial in the city of quincy, running from quincy ave to the furnace brook parkway.
taunton-new bedford expressway\n(alfred m. bessette memorial highway)
the new bedford expressway comprises the southern 19 miles (31 km) of route 140, and serves as a freeway connection between u.s. route 6 in new bedford and route 24 (exit 12) in taunton, near i-495.
route 9 in framingham is named the ted williams highway, in commemoration of late boston red sox hall-of-famer ted williams who wore the number 9 on his jersey.
i-84 in massachusetts is designated the wilbur cross highway. it runs 8 miles (13 km) from the connecticut state border to the mass pike at exit 9.

route 146 is a freeway that, along with rhode island's route 146, serves to connect the metropolitan areas of providence and worcester. the entire route starts from i-95 in providence, with the massachusetts section picking up at the state line in millville. the highway runs 21 miles (34 km) northward, intersecting the mass pike (i-90) in worcester, and terminating at i-290 shortly thereafter.\n- route 122a runs along the highway between exits 9 and 12, concurrently with route 146.

the yankee division highway consists of the route 128 beltway before it was truncated to its southern terminus in canton, and continues to span its entire length. it stretches from i-93's exit 7 in braintree to route 128's northern terminus at route 127a in gloucester.

which episode has the summary that involves the fantastic four dealing with an impostor posing as a hollywood director?
table_text: the fantastic four are off to carry out their experiments on a remote island. the mole man, however, has been waiting for them and traps them in a radiation field and plans to submerge the world’s largest cities. the fantastic four escape but the mole man traps them again. they manage to escape their separate ways. they foil mole man’s domination and escape the island once and for all.

the fantastic four find a ruined castle in the middle of a forest in transylvania. ben is summoned by diablo and unable to resist, opens diablo's prison, unleashing him and later brainwashing ben. diablo tricks the world into thinking he has the power to help them. the world then realises what a fraud diablo really is. the fantastic four seize this opportunity to attack diablo’s castle. after getting far in the dungeons, the four get captured. ben escapes, releases the others and they defeat diablo.

while on a television show, reed recalls the time he first met victor von doom before he became dr. doom. he had ben as his roommate at university. victor was working on dangerous experiments, especially a test that brought him to the hospital and got him expelled from university. worse than that, the test altered his face and he swore revenge on reed having to hide his work from him. ben and reed became soldiers in world war ii. ben, susan, johnny and reed all went aboard a space rocket for space exploration. and so the origin of the fantastic four began. dr. doom confronts the fantastic four on the television show and briefs them on his origin. after that dr. doom attempts to get his revenge, but fails and escapes only to crash.

the skrulls have immediately failed to destroy the fantastic four. they introduce the super-skrull who possesses double power effects the fantastic four have. the fantastic four are overwhelmed by the super-skrull’s combined powers. the fantastic four lure the super-skrull to crater island. susan plants a sonic wave jamming device on the super-skrull before he can destroy them with his ultimate power level.
klaw is here to vanquish the fantastic 4 with his solidifying sonic waves. johnny is on vacation or so it would seem and arrives in the nick of time to assist mr. fantastic in catching the klaw.

reed is competing with dr. kragoff in race to the moon for astronomical research. during the launch, dr. kragoff and his primate crew have developed some reverse energy powers. dr. kragoff is now transparent and becomes the red ghost. red ghost kidnaps susan after counter attacking. she escapes and thwarts red ghost’s attempt to eliminate her companions. using a special device, reed turns red ghost into a plastic statue.

a ufo has been sighted. the pilot abducts the fantastic four from the science center and is setting course for planet x. there, their dictator kurrgo requests the fantastic four save their planet from another planet knocked off its orbit. reed manages to formulate a working plan to save the population. while the plan is in process, kurrgo has other ideas. however, reed tricks kurrgo and leaves him on the exploding planet while the micro-sized population and the fantastic four get away to safety.

the fantastic four face a bunch of old rivals in yancy street, but their old enemy red ghost and his primates show up and capture them. during their voyage to the moon, the four turn the tables, but red ghost gets away and the four are dumped on the moon. they barely manage to get to a source of oxygen which is the watcher’s laboratory. using one of the watcher’s machines, reed brings down red ghost’s ship. susan gets dr. kragoff banished into a trans-nitron machine. reed uses that machine to get back to earth.

dr. doom challenges the fantastic four. doctor doom begins his plans by capturing susan. soon the fantastic four manage to locate and penetrate dr. doom’s flying fortress, but ben is turned back to his former self and the other three are trapped. ben turns himself back into the thing, releases the others and aborts dr. doom’s tidal waves. they chase dr. doom out and back to the flying fortress. after a struggle through the dangerous complex of the fortress, they abort dr. doom’s global destruction for good.

the fantastic four are testing their rocket when they are drawn into the skrull galaxy. after beating the first round of skrulls, the fantastic four weaken and are taken prisoner. the cruel skrull warlord morrat wishes to overthrow the skrull emperor. the warlord gives the fantastic four the option to assist them or die. reed tricks the warlord into getting him and his friends' powers fully charged. they defeat the warlord as the emperor arrives and he allows the fantastic 4 to go freely back to earth.

the fantastic four beat the criminal forces working for dr. gamma, and blow up the island with its secret weapons. while escaping, dr. gamma is infected by the radiation levels in the seabed and morphs into some creature. johnny is flustered with being moved around and quits from the fantastic four. in the town johnny goes to, there have been sightings of the gamma ray. johnny defeats the gamma ray by himself, but he comes back with the hideous giant sea monster giganto. johnny rejoins the fantastic four. ben succeeds in eliminating the sea monster. the gamma ray is defeated but not finished.

johnny finds a mysterious lady named lady dorma and takes her back to the headquarters. she claims to have come from a land beneath the sea called pacifica, which is under siege by attuma. they manage to slip past attuma’s forces. pacifica is losing hope and attuma has shadowed the seabed. triton can only fight man-to-man with attuma while his men prepare traps to weaken triton into a losing battle. the fantastic 4 thwart every trap. triton beats attuma and the forces retreat. note: due to the rights to the sub-mariner being held by grantray-lawrence animation, the adaptation of the first meeting between the ff and namor was altered. instead, prince triton, an original pastiche of namor was reworked into the namor role.

the mole man is creating earthquakes and causing buildings to sink deep into the earth. in addition, he and his moloids kidnap susan. the mole man as usual has been expecting the other three and sends them back to the surface to tell the army not to get involved. they manage to halt them and seek an alternate entrance in the underworld. johnny rescues susan, then they penetrate the laboratory. they all return the buildings to the surface and escape the exploding caves.

after coming back from vacation reed tells ben an interesting theory on attempting to restore him. they head to dr. doom’s deserted castle to use the time machine the doctor left behind. in 2000 b.c the four weaken during a fight and are taken by pharaoh rama-tut, who is a lot more than he would seem at first sight. susan is to be rama-tut’s queen while the other three are put to work with some mind control. ben turns back to his former self. as he rescues susan, he is once again the thing. the four battle rama-tut to his sphinx. finally, they destroy his sphinx and return to their own time.

the watcher has made strange events in hope of preventing the silver surfer from coming but the plan fails and the surfer summons galactus. susan assists the unconscious surfer and he begins to think differently. the watcher has a plan only johnny can undergo. reed and ben sabotage galactus' earth draining machine and the silver surfer arrives to battle galactus. this angers galactus, but johnny gets back with the weapon that makes galactus see reason not to destroy the earth. note: in the episode "galactus", susan richards (the invisible girl) has the role originated by alicia masters (explaining to the silver surfer about humanity).
the micro world of dr. doom

the fantastic four have been shrunken to small size. dr. doom is after them and takes them to the micro world. dr. doom briefs them on his micro genius experiments involving a king and a princess from the micro world. the four battle the giant guards but dr. doom catches them and imprisons them with the king and princess. they all escape and enlarge themselves. ben puts a stop to the lizard men, then the four return to their own world.

on a remote planet, its inhabitants are fighting against blastaar and are able to banish him. reed and johnny enter the dangerous space zone via dimensional transport. as they depart, blastaar escapes and follows them. blastaar is too powerful for the four to handle. they lure blastaar into an evacuated atomic power plant, where they use some atomic matter to put him in a coma. they eject him through the dimensional transport back into the space zone.

the fantastic four study a radiated meteor. the molecule man appears and threatens the public. after the fantastic four tastes some of his power, he leaves to undergo his ruling the world. reed has developed a weapon he thinks will defeat the molecule man. the weapon works, but the molecule man gets away. the fantastic four continue their pursuit. the plan to stop the molecule man is tricky. they manage to reverse the molecule man’s form with a fragment of the meteor.

the fantastic four are taken to another planet where they are regarded as criminals against evil, charged by three old enemies. reed is forced to recall his memories on klaw, molecule, man and blastaar’s defeat. meanwhile the other three escape and they rescue reed just as the verdict is given. at the surface, they have to battle the court judge before they are able to leave the planet for earth.

the imposter plans to lure the fantastic four into a trap by posing as a famous hollywood director. the four are tempted to be in a movie and briefly retell their previous adventures to the director. the next day, the four fly to the director’s island and the director blows them out of the sky. the fantastic four are forced to go through the director’s deadly movie landscapes and make it to the boat on the other side of the island which the director detonates. the imposter removes his disguise and the fantastic four surprise him. the real director prevents the imposter from escaping upon forgetting that he had locked the director in the room that imposter was escaping into. the fantastic four have no desire to be movie stars in the end.

the fantastic four visit a college where mysterious events take place. professor mindbender, using a powerful device, controls the student body. the team infiltrates the campus and faces several students under mindbender’s control. with teamwork and clever tactics, they disable the device and free the students. mindbender escapes but the campus returns to normal.

a new villain, the shadow, arrives in town, wreaking havoc with his darkness manipulation powers. the fantastic four struggle to confront him as he shrouds the city in total darkness. with reed’s invention, they manage to generate a light strong enough to counteract the shadows. the shadow withdraws, promising to return with greater strength.

dr. doom creates a new legion of androids to take down the fantastic four. the androids invade the city, causing chaos. the fantastic four are pushed to their limits until reed devises a way to short circuit their systems. in a final battle at doom's hidden lair, they defeat the androids but doom escapes, vowing revenge.

the team encounters an artifact, the cosmic gauntlet, which grants its wielder immense power. dr. doom gets hold of the gauntlet first and challenges the fantastic four. the team discovers the gauntlet has a weakness to their combined powers. they use this knowledge to dismantle the gauntlet's power and stop doom’s plans.

the time stream becomes unstable, causing time disruptions across new york city. reed traces the disturbance to an old rival playing with a powerful time manipulator. the team travels through various time periods to stop him, eventually fixing the disruptor and restoring the timeline. however, relics from different times appear mysteriously in the present.

the fantastic four face a dire challenge as a new villain, grimlord, takes ben's powers away temporarily. questioning his place on the team, ben discovers inner strengths as reed finds a way to restore him. with ben back in the fight, they overpower grimlord, restoring balance to their world.

four elemental beings attack the city, each controlling air, water, earth, or fire. the fantastic four split up to tackle each foe but realize they must unite their efforts. through creative teamwork, they neutralize the elemental onslaught. the beings retreat, revealing they were only the first wave of a larger invasion.

what episode involves the fantastic four battling a villain called the molecule man?
table_text: the fantastic four are off to carry out their experiments on a remote island. the mole man, however, has been waiting for them and traps them in a radiation field and plans to submerge the world’s largest cities. the fantastic four escape but the mole man traps them again. they manage to escape their separate ways. they foil mole man’s domination and escape the island once and for all.

the fantastic four find a ruined castle in the middle of a forest in transylvania. ben is summoned by diablo and unable to resist, opens diablo's prison, unleashing him and later brainwashing ben. diablo tricks the world into thinking he has the power to help them. the world then realises what a fraud diablo really is. the fantastic four seize this opportunity to attack diablo’s castle. after getting far in the dungeons, the four get captured. ben escapes, releases the others and they defeat diablo.

while on a television show, reed recalls the time he first met victor von doom before he became dr. doom. he had ben as his roommate at university. victor was working on dangerous experiments, especially a test that brought him to the hospital and got him expelled from university. worse than that, the test altered his face and he swore revenge on reed having to hide his work from him. ben and reed became soldiers in world war ii. ben, susan, johnny and reed all went aboard a space rocket for space exploration. and so the origin of the fantastic four began. dr. doom confronts the fantastic four on the television show and briefs them on his origin. after that dr. doom attempts to get his revenge, but fails and escapes only to crash.

the skrulls have immediately failed to destroy the fantastic four. they introduce the super-skrull who possesses double power effects the fantastic four have. the fantastic four are overwhelmed by the super-skrull’s combined powers. the fantastic four lure the super-skrull to crater island. susan plants a sonic wave jamming device on the super-skrull before he can destroy them with his ultimate power level.
klaw is here to vanquish the fantastic 4 with his solidifying sonic waves. johnny is on vacation or so it would seem and arrives in the nick of time to assist mr. fantastic in catching the klaw.

reed is competing with dr. kragoff in race to the moon for astronomical research. during the launch, dr. kragoff and his primate crew have developed some reverse energy powers. dr. kragoff is now transparent and becomes the red ghost. red ghost kidnaps susan after counter attacking. she escapes and thwarts red ghost’s attempt to eliminate her companions. using a special device, reed turns red ghost into a plastic statue.

a ufo has been sighted. the pilot abducts the fantastic four from the science center and is setting course for planet x. there, their dictator kurrgo requests the fantastic four save their planet from another planet knocked off its orbit. reed manages to formulate a working plan to save the population. while the plan is in process, kurrgo has other ideas. however, reed tricks kurrgo and leaves him on the exploding planet while the micro-sized population and the fantastic four get away to safety.

the fantastic four face a bunch of old rivals in yancy street, but their old enemy red ghost and his primates show up and capture them. during their voyage to the moon, the four turn the tables, but red ghost gets away and the four are dumped on the moon. they barely manage to get to a source of oxygen which is the watcher’s laboratory. using one of the watcher’s machines, reed brings down red ghost’s ship. susan gets dr. kragoff banished into a trans-nitron machine. reed uses that machine to get back to earth.

dr. doom challenges the fantastic four. doctor doom begins his plans by capturing susan. soon the fantastic four manage to locate and penetrate dr. doom’s flying fortress, but ben is turned back to his former self and the other three are trapped. ben turns himself back into the thing, releases the others and aborts dr. doom’s tidal waves. they chase dr. doom out and back to the flying fortress. after a struggle through the dangerous complex of the fortress, they abort dr. doom’s global destruction for good.

the fantastic four are testing their rocket when they are drawn into the skrull galaxy. after beating the first round of skrulls, the fantastic four weaken and are taken prisoner. the cruel skrull warlord morrat wishes to overthrow the skrull emperor. the warlord gives the fantastic four the option to assist them or die. reed tricks the warlord into getting him and his friends' powers fully charged. they defeat the warlord as the emperor arrives and he allows the fantastic 4 to go freely back to earth.

the fantastic four beat the criminal forces working for dr. gamma, and blow up the island with its secret weapons. while escaping, dr. gamma is infected by the radiation levels in the seabed and morphs into some creature. johnny is flustered with being moved around and quits from the fantastic four. in the town johnny goes to, there have been sightings of the gamma ray. johnny defeats the gamma ray by himself, but he comes back with the hideous giant sea monster giganto. johnny rejoins the fantastic four. ben succeeds in eliminating the sea monster. the gamma ray is defeated but not finished.

johnny finds a mysterious lady named lady dorma and takes her back to the headquarters. she claims to have come from a land beneath the sea called pacifica, which is under siege by attuma. they manage to slip past attuma’s forces. pacifica is losing hope and attuma has shadowed the seabed. triton can only fight man-to-man with attuma while his men prepare traps to weaken triton into a losing battle. the fantastic 4 thwart every trap. triton beats attuma and the forces retreat. note: due to the rights to the sub-mariner being held by grantray-lawrence animation, the adaptation of the first meeting between the ff and namor was altered. instead, prince triton, an original pastiche of namor was reworked into the namor role.

the mole man is creating earthquakes and causing buildings to sink deep into the earth. in addition, he and his moloids kidnap susan. the mole man as usual has been expecting the other three and sends them back to the surface to tell the army not to get involved. they manage to halt them and seek an alternate entrance in the underworld. johnny rescues susan, then they penetrate the laboratory. they all return the buildings to the surface and escape the exploding caves.

after coming back from vacation reed tells ben an interesting theory on attempting to restore him. they head to dr. doom’s deserted castle to use the time machine the doctor left behind. in 2000 b.c the four weaken during a fight and are taken by pharaoh rama-tut, who is a lot more than he would seem at first sight. susan is to be rama-tut’s queen while the other three are put to work with some mind control. ben turns back to his former self. as he rescues susan, he is once again the thing. the four battle rama-tut to his sphinx. finally, they destroy his sphinx and return to their own time.

the watcher has made strange events in hope of preventing the silver surfer from coming but the plan fails and the surfer summons galactus. susan assists the unconscious surfer and he begins to think differently. the watcher has a plan only johnny can undergo. reed and ben sabotage galactus' earth draining machine and the silver surfer arrives to battle galactus. this angers galactus, but johnny gets back with the weapon that makes galactus see reason not to destroy the earth. note: in the episode "galactus", susan richards (the invisible girl) has the role originated by alicia masters (explaining to the silver surfer about humanity).
the micro world of dr. doom

the fantastic four have been shrunken to small size. dr. doom is after them and takes them to the micro world. dr. doom briefs them on his micro genius experiments involving a king and a princess from the micro world. the four battle the giant guards but dr. doom catches them and imprisons them with the king and princess. they all escape and enlarge themselves. ben puts a stop to the lizard men, then the four return to their own world.

on a remote planet, its inhabitants are fighting against blastaar and are able to banish him. reed and johnny enter the dangerous space zone via dimensional transport. as they depart, blastaar escapes and follows them. blastaar is too powerful for the four to handle. they lure blastaar into an evacuated atomic power plant, where they use some atomic matter to put him in a coma. they eject him through the dimensional transport back into the space zone.

the fantastic four study a radiated meteor. the molecule man appears and threatens the public. after the fantastic four tastes some of his power, he leaves to undergo his ruling the world. reed has developed a weapon he thinks will defeat the molecule man. the weapon works, but the molecule man gets away. the fantastic four continue their pursuit. the plan to stop the molecule man is tricky. they manage to reverse the molecule man’s form with a fragment of the meteor.

the fantastic four are taken to another planet where they are regarded as criminals against evil, charged by three old enemies. reed is forced to recall his memories on klaw, molecule, man and blastaar’s defeat. meanwhile the other three escape and they rescue reed just as the verdict is given. at the surface, they have to battle the court judge before they are able to leave the planet for earth.

the imposter plans to lure the fantastic four into a trap by posing as a famous hollywood director. the four are tempted to be in a movie and briefly retell their previous adventures to the director. the next day, the four fly to the director’s island and the director blows them out of the sky. the fantastic four are forced to go through the director’s deadly movie landscapes and make it to the boat on the other side of the island which the director detonates. the imposter removes his disguise and the fantastic four surprise him. the real director prevents the imposter from escaping upon forgetting that he had locked the director in the room that imposter was escaping into. the fantastic four have no desire to be movie stars in the end.

galactus returns to earth seeking revenge on the fantastic four. he plans to drain the earth of all its energy. the fantastic four must team up with the silver surfer to stop this catastrophic event. together, they discover a weakness in galactus' armor and manage to repel him back into space using the cosmic power of the surfer.

the fantastic four are summoned to outer space by the galactic council to investigate strange nightmares plaguing the universe's most powerful leaders. they uncover a truth-shattering prophecy orchestrated by a villain who feeds on fear, known as the dream weaver. they must confront their own fears to defeat him and save the galaxy.

the earth is threatened by a new supervillain, the elemental, who can control the weather and natural disasters. the fantastic four must battle his elemental forces in different locations around the world. with teamwork and innovation, they manage to neutralize his powers by using technology to harmonize the earth's energies.

the fantastic four encounter a formless entity from another dimension that consumes anything that possesses structure. as chaos ensues, the team must race against time to find a way to contain the formless void before it devours the entire city. they succeed by using a device that emits a frequency which contorts the entity, sending it back through the dimensional rift.

when two powerful beings, ares and thor, clash on earth over an ancient conflict, the fantastic four are caught in the middle. they must find a way to broker peace between the gods and prevent their battle from destroying the world. with diplomacy and strategy, they manage to remind the gods of their shared past and bring an end to their war.

statement: which episode's summary involves a mythical dragon and an ancient sorcerer?
table_text: the fantastic four are off to carry out their experiments on a remote island. the mole man, however, has been waiting for them and traps them in a radiation field and plans to submerge the world’s largest cities. the fantastic four escape but the mole man traps them again. they manage to escape their separate ways. they foil mole man’s domination and escape the island once and for all.

the fantastic four find a ruined castle in the middle of a forest in transylvania. ben is summoned by diablo and unable to resist, opens diablo's prison, unleashing him and later brainwashing ben. diablo tricks the world into thinking he has the power to help them. the world then realises what a fraud diablo really is. the fantastic four seize this opportunity to attack diablo’s castle. after getting far in the dungeons, the four get captured. ben escapes, releases the others and they defeat diablo.

while on a television show, reed recalls the time he first met victor von doom before he became dr. doom. he had ben as his roommate at university. victor was working on dangerous experiments, especially a test that brought him to the hospital and got him expelled from university. worse than that, the test altered his face and he swore revenge on reed having to hide his work from him. ben and reed became soldiers in world war ii. ben, susan, johnny and reed all went aboard a space rocket for space exploration. and so the origin of the fantastic four began. dr. doom confronts the fantastic four on the television show and briefs them on his origin. after that dr. doom attempts to get his revenge, but fails and escapes only to crash.

the skrulls have immediately failed to destroy the fantastic four. they introduce the super-skrull who possesses double power effects the fantastic four have. the fantastic four are overwhelmed by the super-skrull’s combined powers. the fantastic four lure the super-skrull to crater island. susan plants a sonic wave jamming device on the super-skrull before he can destroy them with his ultimate power level.
klaw is here to vanquish the fantastic 4 with his solidifying sonic waves. johnny is on vacation or so it would seem and arrives in the nick of time to assist mr. fantastic in catching the klaw.

reed is competing with dr. kragoff in race to the moon for astronomical research. during the launch, dr. kragoff and his primate crew have developed some reverse energy powers. dr. kragoff is now transparent and becomes the red ghost. red ghost kidnaps susan after counter attacking. she escapes and thwarts red ghost’s attempt to eliminate her companions. using a special device, reed turns red ghost into a plastic statue.

a ufo has been sighted. the pilot abducts the fantastic four from the science center and is setting course for planet x. there, their dictator kurrgo requests the fantastic four save their planet from another planet knocked off its orbit. reed manages to formulate a working plan to save the population. while the plan is in process, kurrgo has other ideas. however, reed tricks kurrgo and leaves him on the exploding planet while the micro-sized population and the fantastic four get away to safety.

the fantastic four face a bunch of old rivals in yancy street, but their old enemy red ghost and his primates show up and capture them. during their voyage to the moon, the four turn the tables, but red ghost gets away and the four are dumped on the moon. they barely manage to get to a source of oxygen which is the watcher’s laboratory. using one of the watcher’s machines, reed brings down red ghost’s ship. susan gets dr. kragoff banished into a trans-nitron machine. reed uses that machine to get back to earth.

dr. doom challenges the fantastic four. doctor doom begins his plans by capturing susan. soon the fantastic four manage to locate and penetrate dr. doom’s flying fortress, but ben is turned back to his former self and the other three are trapped. ben turns himself back into the thing, releases the others and aborts dr. doom’s tidal waves. they chase dr. doom out and back to the flying fortress. after a struggle through the dangerous complex of the fortress, they abort dr. doom’s global destruction for good.

the fantastic four are testing their rocket when they are drawn into the skrull galaxy. after beating the first round of skrulls, the fantastic four weaken and are taken prisoner. the cruel skrull warlord morrat wishes to overthrow the skrull emperor. the warlord gives the fantastic four the option to assist them or die. reed tricks the warlord into getting him and his friends' powers fully charged. they defeat the warlord as the emperor arrives and he allows the fantastic 4 to go freely back to earth.

the fantastic four beat the criminal forces working for dr. gamma, and blow up the island with its secret weapons. while escaping, dr. gamma is infected by the radiation levels in the seabed and morphs into some creature. johnny is flustered with being moved around and quits from the fantastic four. in the town johnny goes to, there have been sightings of the gamma ray. johnny defeats the gamma ray by himself, but he comes back with the hideous giant sea monster giganto. johnny rejoins the fantastic four. ben succeeds in eliminating the sea monster. the gamma ray is defeated but not finished.

johnny finds a mysterious lady named lady dorma and takes her back to the headquarters. she claims to have come from a land beneath the sea called pacifica, which is under siege by attuma. they manage to slip past attuma’s forces. pacifica is losing hope and attuma has shadowed the seabed. triton can only fight man-to-man with attuma while his men prepare traps to weaken triton into a losing battle. the fantastic 4 thwart every trap. triton beats attuma and the forces retreat. note: due to the rights to the sub-mariner being held by grantray-lawrence animation, the adaptation of the first meeting between the ff and namor was altered. instead, prince triton, an original pastiche of namor was reworked into the namor role.

the mole man is creating earthquakes and causing buildings to sink deep into the earth. in addition, he and his moloids kidnap susan. the mole man as usual has been expecting the other three and sends them back to the surface to tell the army not to get involved. they manage to halt them and seek an alternate entrance in the underworld. johnny rescues susan, then they penetrate the laboratory. they all return the buildings to the surface and escape the exploding caves.

after coming back from vacation reed tells ben an interesting theory on attempting to restore him. they head to dr. doom’s deserted castle to use the time machine the doctor left behind. in 2000 b.c the four weaken during a fight and are taken by pharaoh rama-tut, who is a lot more than he would seem at first sight. susan is to be rama-tut’s queen while the other three are put to work with some mind control. ben turns back to his former self. as he rescues susan, he is once again the thing. the four battle rama-tut to his sphinx. finally, they destroy his sphinx and return to their own time.

the watcher has made strange events in hope of preventing the silver surfer from coming but the plan fails and the surfer summons galactus. susan assists the unconscious surfer and he begins to think differently. the watcher has a plan only johnny can undergo. reed and ben sabotage galactus' earth draining machine and the silver surfer arrives to battle galactus. this angers galactus, but johnny gets back with the weapon that makes galactus see reason not to destroy the earth. note: in the episode "galactus", susan richards (the invisible girl) has the role originated by alicia masters (explaining to the silver surfer about humanity).
the micro world of dr. doom

the fantastic four have been shrunken to small size. dr. doom is after them and takes them to the micro world. dr. doom briefs them on his micro genius experiments involving a king and a princess from the micro world. the four battle the giant guards but dr. doom catches them and imprisons them with the king and princess. they all escape and enlarge themselves. ben puts a stop to the lizard men, then the four return to their own world.

on a remote planet, its inhabitants are fighting against blastaar and are able to banish him. reed and johnny enter the dangerous space zone via dimensional transport. as they depart, blastaar escapes and follows them. blastaar is too powerful for the four to handle. they lure blastaar into an evacuated atomic power plant, where they use some atomic matter to put him in a coma. they eject him through the dimensional transport back into the space zone.

the fantastic four study a radiated meteor. the molecule man appears and threatens the public. after the fantastic four tastes some of his power, he leaves to undergo his ruling the world. reed has developed a weapon he thinks will defeat the molecule man. the weapon works, but the molecule man gets away. the fantastic four continue their pursuit. the plan to stop the molecule man is tricky. they manage to reverse the molecule man’s form with a fragment of the meteor.

the fantastic four are taken to another planet where they are regarded as criminals against evil, charged by three old enemies. reed is forced to recall his memories on klaw, molecule, man and blastaar’s defeat. meanwhile the other three escape and they rescue reed just as the verdict is given. at the surface, they have to battle the court judge before they are able to leave the planet for earth.

the imposter plans to lure the fantastic four into a trap by posing as a famous hollywood director. the four are tempted to be in a movie and briefly retell their previous adventures to the director. the next day, the four fly to the director’s island and the director blows them out of the sky. the fantastic four are forced to go through the director’s deadly movie landscapes and make it to the boat on the other side of the island which the director detonates. the imposter removes his disguise and the fantastic four surprise him. the real director prevents the imposter from escaping upon forgetting that he had locked the director in the room that imposter was escaping into. the fantastic four have no desire to be movie stars in the end.

the fantastic four are drawn to a mysterious island where a mythical dragon is terrorizing the inhabitants. the team discovers that the dragon is controlled by an ancient sorcerer seeking revenge on the modern world. the fantastic four must work together to break the sorcerer's hold on the dragon and save the island.

while testing a new inventions, reed accidentally opens a time portal, sending the fantastic four into different eras. they must navigate through various historical challenges and reunite before the portal closes. during their journey, they learn valuable lessons that help them become a stronger team.

a futuristic city suddenly appears in the middle of manhattan, created by an advanced alien civilization looking to establish a new home. the fantastic four must negotiate with the alien leader to prevent a war with humanity. they eventually find a peaceful solution, and the aliens agree to relocate to a remote island.

earth's natural elements are mysteriously going haywire, causing disasters around the globe. the fantastic four track the disturbances to an underground lab where a rogue scientist is experimenting with a device to control the world's elements. they confront and defeat the scientist, restoring balance to the planet.

new york city is plagued by an army of living shadows causing chaos at night. the fantastic four discover the shadows are being animated by a powerful device controlled by a vengeful former villain. they must navigate through the shadow-infested city to disable the device and save the day.

world leaders are falling into inexplicable comas, trapped in a dream world created by a mysterious figure known as the dream thief. the fantastic four embark on a journey into this dream realm to rescue the leaders and stop the dream thief from taking over reality.

the fantastic four receive a tip about an ancient city of gold hidden in the amazon rainforest. they set out on an expedition, battling dangerous obstacles and rival treasure hunters. upon finding the city, they release a curse that turns the hunters to stone, forcing the fantastic four to solve an ancient puzzle to make things right.

a mysterious artifact causes the fantastic four to encounter evil duplicates of themselves. these mirror versions attempt to take over their lives and wreak havoc. the original team must defeat their duplicates by understanding their own weaknesses and strengths, ultimately learning to trust each other more.

reports of a swamp monster terrorizing a southern town reach the fantastic four. after investigating, they learn that the creature is a misunderstood guardian of the bayou. with the help of a local researcher, they clear the creature's name and help it communicate with the townsfolk.

which route has the longest length on this list?
table_text: runs from concord avenue to the mystic valley parkway.
runs through tiverton, rhode island; fall river, massachusetts; westport, massachusetts

route 24 is a connector between the fall river/new bedford area east of rhode island to the boston metropolitan area, connecting the major freeways of the area: i-195 in fall river and i-93/us-1 near i-95 in randolph.\n- route 79 runs along the highway between exits 7 and 9, concurrent with route 24.\n- i-195 has a brief concurrency with route 24 in fall river.
most of us-20 between marlborough and weston runs along the boston post road.
freeway comprises the eastern 5 miles (8.0 km) of route 57, connecting route 187 to u.s. route 5 and i-91.

route 9 between worcester and boston is mostly a divided full-access highway with traffic light-controlled intersections which serves as one of the main alternatives to the massachusetts turnpike. many shopping centers, car dealers, full-service restaurants and businesses line the roadway on this stretch, especially in framingham, such as barnes & noble, marshalls, t.g.i. fridays, kohl's, toys "r" us, best buy, olive garden and walmart. this stretch of the roadway is also encompassed in the golden triangle district of massachusetts.

the central artery is the portion of i-93 in downtown boston, which runs from massachusetts ave. (just south of exit 20) north to u.s. route 1's departure at exit 27.\nroute 3 leaves the artery at exit 26.
stretches from weston/newton line to the boston public garden.

the east boston expressway comprises the first 1.2 miles (1.9 km) of route 1a's northern segment. it stretches from i-93 exit 24 at the southern end of the callahan tunnel (northbound) and the sumner tunnel (southbound) to just northeast of the interchange with route 145 in east boston, near the eastern end of the mass pike.
grand army of the republic highway
the cross-country u.s. route 6 is designated grand army of the republic highway over its entire length, which spans 3,205 miles (5,158 km).
route 88 serves as a connector running from the horseneck beach reservation north to i-195 exit 10 in westport.
route 213 is designated "loop connector." it serves as a freeway connection between interstates 93 and 495 in methuen.
route 146a in massachusetts is designated as the lydia taft highway, which runs from the rhode island state border to route 122 in uxbridge.

the mass pike is a toll road running from the new york state border to downtown boston. it serves as the main cross-state freeway connecting the western and eastern portions of the state. the "pike" carries the easternmost 138 miles (222 km) of cross-country interstate 90.

u.s. route 3 and ma route 3 connect to each other on memorial drive, which runs from the fresh pond parkway to main street.\nroute 2 travels along memorial drive with us-3 and leaves via the boston university bridge.
the mid-cape highway is the main highway on cape cod, a 36-mile (58 km) long freeway running from route 3 and the sagamore bridge east to the orleans rotary.
the 65-mile (105 km) mohawk trail comprises the western section of route 2, from the new york border east to orange, and is regarded as one of the most scenic drives in the area.
runs from the alewife brook parkway to the revere beach parkway.

this section of u.s. route 1 runs from i-93 exit 27 (tobin bridge) to an interchange with route 60 in revere. this was originally supposed to be part of i-95, but i-95 was cancelled in boston, with i-93 and us-1 taking its place.
the northwest expressway serves as a freeway connection between i-95/route 128 (exit 32a) in burlington and the f.e. everett turnpike in nashua, nh.

the pilgrims highway is the southern portion of route 3, a 42-mile (68 km) long freeway which serves as a connector between cape cod (via u.s. route 6) and the boston metropolitan area (via i-93 and i-95).\n- u.s. route 44 runs along the highway between exits 6 and 7.
the southeast expressway is the section of i-93 between the route 3 split (exit 7) and the mass ave. interchange (exit 18), where it continues into boston as the central artery.
the southern artery is a major arterial in the city of quincy, running from quincy ave to the furnace brook parkway.
taunton-new bedford expressway\n(alfred m. bessette memorial highway)
the new bedford expressway comprises the southern 19 miles (31 km) of route 140, and serves as a freeway connection between u.s. route 6 in new bedford and route 24 (exit 12) in taunton, near i-495.
route 9 in framingham is named the ted williams highway, in commemoration of late boston red sox hall-of-famer ted williams who wore the number 9 on his jersey.
i-84 in massachusetts is designated the wilbur cross highway. it runs 8 miles (13 km) from the connecticut state border to the mass pike at exit 9.

route 146 is a freeway that, along with rhode island's route 146, serves to connect the metropolitan areas of providence and worcester. the entire route starts from i-95 in providence, with the massachusetts section picking up at the state line in millville. the highway runs 21 miles (34 km) northward, intersecting the mass pike (i-90) in worcester, and terminating at i-290 shortly thereafter.\n- route 122a runs along the highway between exits 9 and 12, concurrently with route 146.

the yankee division highway consists of the route 128 beltway before it was truncated to its southern terminus in canton, and continues to span its entire length. it stretches from i-93's exit 7 in braintree to route 128's northern terminus at route 127a in gloucester.
- i-95 runs along the highway between exits 12 and 45 (concurrent with 128).
- i-93 runs along the highway between exits 1 and 7.
- u.s. route 1 runs along the highway between i-95 exit 15b and i-93 exit 7.
parallels the cape cod canal from the bourne bridge to the sandwich beach area.
runs mostly concurrent with route 6 from the sagamore bridge to barnstable, serving as an extension of the mid-cape highway.
the quincy-shore expressway is part of the north-south traffic alleviation route connecting i-93 to the quincy shore drive.
follows the southern part of route 3 along the merrimack river through historic areas and connects to the everett turnpike in nashua.
bypasses downtown westfield by connecting route 10 and route 202 with i-90.
known as a section of u.s. route 146, it provides a scenic option between the major metropolitan areas.
links the boston inner loop with the redwood park district, offering quick access through congested areas.
operates as an auxiliary link from i-495 to i-93, making interstate travel easier between massachusetts and new hampshire.
serves as an east-west bypass connecting brockton to the eastern side's major routes and coastal areas.
an island road that connects downtown nantucket with surfside beach, passing by various coastal attractions.

the mole man is creating earthquakes and causing buildings to sink deep into the earth. in addition, he and his moloids kidnap susan. the mole man as usual has been expecting the other three and sends them back to the surface to tell the army not to get involved. they manage to halt them and seek an alternate entrance in the underworld. johnny rescues susan, then they penetrate the laboratory. they all return the buildings to the surface and escape the exploding caves.

after coming back from vacation reed tells ben an interesting theory on attempting to restore him. they head to dr. doom’s deserted castle to use the time machine the doctor left behind. in 2000 b.c the four weaken during a fight and are taken by pharaoh rama-tut, who is a lot more than he would seem at first sight. susan is to be rama-tut’s queen while the other three are put to work with some mind control. ben turns back to his former self. as he rescues susan, he is once again the thing. the four battle rama-tut to his sphinx. finally, they destroy his sphinx and return to their own time.

the watcher has made strange events in hope of preventing the silver surfer from coming but the plan fails and the surfer summons galactus. susan assists the unconscious surfer and he begins to think differently. the watcher has a plan only johnny can undergo. reed and ben sabotage galactus' earth draining machine and the silver surfer arrives to battle galactus. this angers galactus, but johnny gets back with the weapon that makes galactus see reason not to destroy the earth. note: in the episode "galactus", susan richards (the invisible girl) has the role originated by alicia masters (explaining to the silver surfer about humanity).
the micro world of dr. doom

the fantastic four have been shrunken to small size. dr. doom is after them and takes them to the micro world. dr. doom briefs them on his micro genius experiments involving a king and a princess from the micro world. the four battle the giant guards but dr. doom catches them and imprisons them with the king and princess. they all escape and enlarge themselves. ben puts a stop to the lizard men, then the four return to their own world.

on a remote planet, its inhabitants are fighting against blastaar and are able to banish him. reed and johnny enter the dangerous space zone via dimensional transport. as they depart, blastaar escapes and follows them. blastaar is too powerful for the four to handle. they lure blastaar into an evacuated atomic power plant, where they use some atomic matter to put him in a coma. they eject him through the dimensional transport back into the space zone.

the fantastic four study a radiated meteor. the molecule man appears and threatens the public. after the fantastic four tastes some of his power, he leaves to undergo his ruling the world. reed has developed a weapon he thinks will defeat the molecule man. the weapon works, but the molecule man gets away. the fantastic four continue their pursuit. the plan to stop the molecule man is tricky. they manage to reverse the molecule man’s form with a fragment of the meteor.

the fantastic four are taken to another planet where they are regarded as criminals against evil, charged by three old enemies. reed is forced to recall his memories on klaw, molecule, man and blastaar’s defeat. meanwhile the other three escape and they rescue reed just as the verdict is given. at the surface, they have to battle the court judge before they are able to leave the planet for earth.

the imposter plans to lure the fantastic four into a trap by posing as a famous hollywood director. the four are tempted to be in a movie and briefly retell their previous adventures to the director. the next day, the four fly to the director’s island and the director blows them out of the sky. the fantastic four are forced to go through the director’s deadly movie landscapes and make it to the boat on the other side of the island which the director detonates. the imposter removes his disguise and the fantastic four surprise him. the real director prevents the imposter from escaping upon forgetting that he had locked the director in the room that imposter was escaping into. the fantastic four have no desire to be movie stars in the end.
the menace from the phantom zone

the fantastic four accidentally open a portal to the phantom zone, unleashing powerful creatures. they work together to push the creatures back and seal the portal, before the zone's instability consumes their reality.

while investigating strange occurrences in the ocean, the fantastic four encounter a giant sea creature raising havoc on ships and nearby islands. using their combined powers, they coax the creature back to the ocean depths, discovering it was being controlled by a hidden device.

dr. doom returns with new allies and technology to exact revenge on the fantastic four. he infiltrates their headquarters and traps them in a nightmare dimension. the fantastic four rally their strength to break free and turn doom’s technology against him.

the sentinel, a cosmic being guarding the galaxy from harm, is coming to judge earth as unworthy. the fantastic four must prove humanity’s potential by facing trials that test their powers, intellect, and heart. after proving earth’s worth, the sentinel leaves to continue his watch over the cosmos.

a new villain named siege lays siege on cities with a powerful force field, demanding surrender. through ingenuity and cooperation with other heroes, the fantastic four uncover and exploit a weakness in the field before confronting siege and dismantling his plans.

ancient gods awaken and challenge the fantastic four to prove themselves worthy protectors of earth. each member faces a god related to their powers and history, learning more about their own strengths and unity, eventually convincing the gods of their rightful place as earth’s champions.

the fantastic four are trapped in a world of illusions and fantasies created by the illusionist. each member must face their deepest fears and desires to break the hold of the illusionist and return to reality, ultimately overcoming the trap through trust in one another.

statement: which episode involves a cosmic entity giving ben unimaginable powers?

the fantastic four find a ruined castle in the middle of a forest in transylvania. ben is summoned by diablo and unable to resist, opens diablo's prison, unleashing him and later brainwashing ben. diablo tricks the world into thinking he has the power to help them. the world then realises what a fraud diablo really is. the fantastic four seize this opportunity to attack diablo’s castle. after getting far in the dungeons, the four get captured. ben escapes, releases the others and they defeat diablo.

while on a television show, reed recalls the time he first met victor von doom before he became dr. doom. he had ben as his roommate at university. victor was working on dangerous experiments, especially a test that brought him to the hospital and got him expelled from university. worse than that, the test altered his face and he swore revenge on reed having to hide his work from him. ben and reed became soldiers in world war ii. ben, susan, johnny and reed all went aboard a space rocket for space exploration. and so the origin of the fantastic four began. dr. doom confronts the fantastic four on the television show and briefs them on his origin. after that dr. doom attempts to get his revenge, but fails and escapes only to crash.

the skrulls have immediately failed to destroy the fantastic four. they introduce the super-skrull who possesses double power effects the fantastic four have. the fantastic four are overwhelmed by the super-skrull’s combined powers. the fantastic four lure the super-skrull to crater island. susan plants a sonic wave jamming device on the super-skrull before he can destroy them with his ultimate power level.
klaw is here to vanquish the fantastic 4 with his solidifying sonic waves. johnny is on vacation or so it would seem and arrives in the nick of time to assist mr. fantastic in catching the klaw.

reed is competing with dr. kragoff in race to the moon for astronomical research. during the launch, dr. kragoff and his primate crew have developed some reverse energy powers. dr. kragoff is now transparent and becomes the red ghost. red ghost kidnaps susan after counter attacking. she escapes and thwarts red ghost’s attempt to eliminate her companions. using a special device, reed turns red ghost into a plastic statue.

a ufo has been sighted. the pilot abducts the fantastic four from the science center and is setting course for planet x. there, their dictator kurrgo requests the fantastic four save their planet from another planet knocked off its orbit. reed manages to formulate a working plan to save the population. while the plan is in process, kurrgo has other ideas. however, reed tricks kurrgo and leaves him on the exploding planet while the micro-sized population and the fantastic four get away to safety.

the fantastic four face a bunch of old rivals in yancy street, but their old enemy red ghost and his primates show up and capture them. during their voyage to the moon, the four turn the tables, but red ghost gets away and the four are dumped on the moon. they barely manage to get to a source of oxygen which is the watcher’s laboratory. using one of the watcher’s machines, reed brings down red ghost’s ship. susan gets dr. kragoff banished into a trans-nitron machine. reed uses that machine to get back to earth.

the fantastic four are accused of treason against earth by an unknown force that has taken control of their headquarters. the team must uncover the mystery behind their accuser while defending themselves against relentless attacks. through teamwork and determination, they clear their names, revealing doom’s latest ploy.

the fantastic four find themselves trapped in a waking nightmare as a new foe, the nightmare king, manipulates their dreams. personal fears manifest into the real world, challenging their strength and unity. with help from each other, they confront the nightmare king and free themselves from his grasp.

reed discovers a portal leading to the mysterious negative zone. despite the dangers, the team explores this new realm and encounters the dictator annihilus. they must find a way back to their own world while dismantling annihilus’ tyrannical rule over the negative zone.

time-traveler zarrko disrupts the present, threatening the fabric of time itself. the fantastic four, with the aid of the watcher, journey across various epochs to thwart zarrko’s plans and restore the time stream. however, zarrko’s schemes reveal unexpected allies in different eras.

a cosmic entity bestows unimaginable powers upon ben, but it comes with a sinister cost. the fantastic four must come to terms with ben’s new abilities and their origins, as they pose a potential danger to earth. ultimately, ben’s sacrifice and courage are keys to saving the day.

an eternal winter threatens to freeze the planet as the villain glacier unleashes his powers. the fantastic four venture to the arctic, battling relentless storms and ice creatures. through an epic showdown, they melt glacier’s heart, ending the everlasting frost and restoring balance to nature.

mysterious aliens disguised as celestial phenomena begin deceiving the world into cooperation. with escalating global chaos, the fantastic four must uncover the truth behind the sky illusions, confronting both world leaders and extraterrestrial imposters before time runs out.

when the fabric of the multiverse starts collapsing, the fantastic four must work with alternate reality versions of themselves to save every dimension. they face countless adversaries from different universes, culminating in a battle against the enigmatic foe behind the multiversal decay.

a mysterious artifact awakens forgotten memories within johnny, leading the fantastic four into a conspiracy linking their past adventures. they venture deep into an ancient alien civilization hidden on earth, revealing secrets that reshape their understanding of their powers and purpose.

an emissary of doom warns of impending catastrophe, creating distrust and suspicion within the fantastic four. facing a ticking clock, they must decide whether to heed the warning or stand their ground, ultimately leading to an unexpected alliance that becomes pivotal in averting global disaster.
